{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["42-LUK-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"LUK"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Luqa \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Good News According to Luqa \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Luqa \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Luk \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Good News According to \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Luqa \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"LUK 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 1:1"},"Since many have undertaken to set in order a narrative concerning those matters which have been fulfilled amongst us,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 1:2"},"even as those who from the beginning were eyewitnesses and servants of the word delivered them to us,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 1:3"},"it seemed good to me also, having traced the course of all things accurately from the first, to write to you in order,\nmost excellent Theophilus; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 1:4"},"that you might know the certainty concerning the things in which you were instructed.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 1:5"},"There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the priestly division of Abijah.\nHe had a wife of the daughters of Harun, and her name was Elizabeth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 1:6"},"They were both righteous before Allah, walking blamelessly in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 1:7"},"But they had no child, because Elizabeth was barren, and they both were well advanced in years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 1:8"},"Now while he executed the priest’s office before Allah in the order of his division,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 1:9"},"according to the custom of the priest’s office, his lot was to enter into the temple of the Lord and burn incense.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 1:10"},"The whole multitude of the people were praying outside at the hour of incense.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 1:11"},"An angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing on the right side of the altar of incense.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 1:12"},"Zacharias was troubled when he saw him, and fear fell upon him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 1:13"},"But the angel said to him, “Don’t be afraid, Zacharias, because your request has been heard, and your wife, Elizabeth,\nwill bear you a son, and you shall call his name Yahya. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 1:14"},"You will have joy and gladness; and many will rejoice at his birth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 1:15"},"For he will be great in the sight of the Lord, and he will drink no wine nor strong drink. He will be filled with the\nHoly Spirit, even from his mother’s womb. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 1:16"},"He will turn many of the children of Israel to the Lord, their Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 1:17"},"He will go before him in the spirit and power of Ilyas, ‘to turn the hearts of the fathers to the\nchildren,’",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Malachi 4:6"]}],"caller":"+"}," and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to prepare a people prepared for the\nLord.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 1:18"},"Zacharias said to the angel, “How can I be sure of this? For I am an old man, and my wife is well advanced in years.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 1:19"},"The angel answered him, “I am Jabreel, who stands in the presence of Allah. I was sent to speak to you, and to bring you\nthis good news. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 1:20"},"Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “ἰδοὺ”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," you will be silent and not able to speak, until the day that these things will happen, because you\ndidn’t believe my words, which will be fulfilled in their proper time.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 1:21"},"The people were waiting for Zacharias, and they marvelled that he delayed in the temple.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 1:22"},"When he came out, he could not speak to them, and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple. He continued\nmaking signs to them, and remained mute. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 1:23"},"When the days of his service were fulfilled, he departed to his house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 1:24"},"After these days Elizabeth, his wife, conceived, and she hid herself five months, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 1:25"},"“Thus has the Lord done to me in the days in which he looked at me, to take away my reproach amongst men.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 1:26"},"Now in the sixth month, the angel Jabreel was sent from Allah to a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 1:27"},"to a virgin pledged to be married to a man whose name was Yusuf, of Dawood’s house. The virgin’s name was Maryam.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 1:28"},"Having come in, the angel said to her, “Rejoice, you highly favoured one! The Lord is with you. Blessed are you amongst\nwomen!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 1:29"},"But when she saw him, she was greatly troubled at the saying, and considered what kind of salutation this might be.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 1:30"},"The angel said to her, “Don’t be afraid, Maryam, for you have found favour with Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 1:31"},"Behold, you will conceive in your womb, and give birth to a son, and will call his name ‘Isa.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 1:32"},"He will be great, and will be called the Son of the Most High. The Lord Allah will give him the throne of his father,\nDawood, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 1:33"},"and he will reign over the house of Yaqub forever. There will be no end to his Kingdom.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 1:34"},"Maryam said to the angel, “How can this be, seeing I am a virgin?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 1:35"},"The angel answered her, “The Holy Spirit will come on you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you. Therefore\nalso the holy one who is born from you will be called the Son of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 1:36"},"Behold, Elizabeth, your relative, also has conceived a son in her old age; and this is the sixth month with her who was\ncalled barren. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 1:37"},"For nothing spoken by Allah is impossible.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, “For everything spoken by Allah is\npossible.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 1:38"},"Maryam said, “Behold, the servant of the Lord; let it be done to me according to your word.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The angel departed from her. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 1:39"},"Maryam arose in those days and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of Judah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 1:40"},"and entered into the house of Zacharias and greeted Elizabeth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 1:41"},"When Elizabeth heard Maryam’s greeting, the baby leapt in her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 1:42"},"She called out with a loud voice, and said, “Blessed are you amongst women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 1:43"},"Why am I so favoured, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 1:44"},"For behold, when the voice of your greeting came into my ears, the baby leapt in my womb for joy!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 1:45"},"Blessed is she who believed, for there will be a fulfilment of the things which have been spoken to her from the Lord!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 1:46"},"Maryam said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“My soul magnifies the Lord. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 1:47"},"My spirit has rejoiced in Allah my Saviour, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 1:48"},"for he has looked at the humble state of his servant. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For behold, from now on, all generations will call me blessed.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 1:49"},"For he who is mighty has done great things for me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Holy is his name. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 1:50"},"His mercy is for generations of generations on those who fear him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 1:51"},"He has shown strength with his arm. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 1:52"},"He has put down princes from their thrones. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["And has exalted the lowly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 1:53"},"He has filled the hungry with good things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has sent the rich away empty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 1:54"},"He has given help to Israel, his servant, that he might remember mercy,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 1:55"},"as he spoke to our fathers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to Ibrahim and his offspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:55 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," forever.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 1:56"},"Maryam stayed with her about three months, and then returned to her house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"LUK 1:57"},"Now the time that Elizabeth should give birth was fulfilled, and she gave birth to a son.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"LUK 1:58"},"Her neighbours and her relatives heard that the Lord had magnified his mercy towards her, and they rejoiced with her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"LUK 1:59"},"On the eighth day, they came to circumcise the child; and they would have called him Zacharias, after the name of his\nfather. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"LUK 1:60"},"His mother answered, “Not so; but he will be called Yahya.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"LUK 1:61"},"They said to her, “There is no one amongst your relatives who is called by this name.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"LUK 1:62"},"They made signs to his father, what he would have him called.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"LUK 1:63"},"He asked for a writing tablet, and wrote, “His name is Yahya.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They all marvelled. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64","sid":"LUK 1:64"},"His mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue freed, and he spoke, blessing Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65","sid":"LUK 1:65"},"Fear came on all who lived around them, and all these sayings were talked about throughout all the hill country of Judea.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66","sid":"LUK 1:66"},"All who heard them laid them up in their heart, saying, “What then will this child be?” The hand of the Lord was with\nhim. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67","sid":"LUK 1:67"},"His father, Zacharias, was filled with the Holy Spirit, and prophesied, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68","sid":"LUK 1:68"},"“Blessed be the Lord, Allah of Israel, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he has visited and redeemed his people; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69","sid":"LUK 1:69"},"and has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant Dawood\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70","sid":"LUK 1:70"},"(as he spoke by the mouth of his holy prophets who have been from of old),\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71","sid":"LUK 1:71"},"salvation from our enemies, and from the hand of all who hate us;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"72","sid":"LUK 1:72"},"to show mercy towards our fathers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to remember his holy covenant, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"73","sid":"LUK 1:73"},"the oath which he swore to Ibrahim, our father, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"74","sid":"LUK 1:74"},"to grant to us that we, being delivered out of the hand of our enemies,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["should serve him without fear, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"75","sid":"LUK 1:75"},"in holiness and righteousness before him all the days of our life.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"76","sid":"LUK 1:76"},"And you, child, will be called a prophet of the Most High,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for you will go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"77","sid":"LUK 1:77"},"to give knowledge of salvation to his people by the remission of their sins,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"78","sid":"LUK 1:78"},"because of the tender mercy of our Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by which the dawn from on high will visit us, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"79","sid":"LUK 1:79"},"to shine on those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to guide our feet into the way of peace.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"80","sid":"LUK 1:80"},"The child was growing, and becoming strong in spirit, and was in the desert until the day of his public appearance to\nIsrael. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"LUK 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 2:1"},"Now in those days, a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that all the world should be enrolled.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 2:2"},"This was the first enrolment made when Quirinius was governor of Syria.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 2:3"},"All went to enrol themselves, everyone to his own city. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 2:4"},"Yusuf also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judea, to Dawood’s city, which is called Bethlehem,\nbecause he was of the house and family of Dawood; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 2:5"},"to enrol himself with Maryam, who was pledged to be married to him as wife, being pregnant.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 2:6"},"While they were there, the day had come for her to give birth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 2:7"},"She gave birth to her firstborn son. She wrapped him in bands of cloth, and laid him in a feeding trough, because there\nwas no room for them in the inn. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 2:8"},"There were shepherds in the same country staying in the field, and keeping watch by night over their flock.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 2:9"},"Behold, an angel of the Lord stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were terrified.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 2:10"},"The angel said to them, “Don’t be afraid, for behold, I bring you good news of great joy which will be to all the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 2:11"},"For there is born to you today, in Dawood’s city, a Saviour, who is Masih the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 2:12"},"This is the sign to you: you will find a baby wrapped in strips of cloth, lying in a feeding trough.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 2:13"},"Suddenly, there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly army praising Allah, and saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 2:14"},"“Glory to Allah in the highest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on earth peace, good will towards men.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 2:15"},"When the angels went away from them into the sky, the shepherds said to one another, “Let’s go to Bethlehem, now, and see\nthis thing that has happened, which the Lord has made known to us.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 2:16"},"They came with haste, and found both Maryam and Yusuf, and the baby was lying in the feeding trough.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 2:17"},"When they saw it, they publicised widely the saying which was spoken to them about this child.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 2:18"},"All who heard it wondered at the things which were spoken to them by the shepherds.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 2:19"},"But Maryam kept all these sayings, pondering them in her heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 2:20"},"The shepherds returned, glorifying and praising Allah for all the things that they had heard and seen, just as it was\ntold them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 2:21"},"When eight days were fulfilled for the circumcision of the child, his name was called Isa, which was given by the angel\nbefore he was conceived in the womb. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 2:22"},"When the days of their purification according to the law of Musa were fulfilled, they brought him up to Jerusalem, to\npresent him to the Lord \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 2:23"},"(as it is written in the law of the Lord, “Every male who opens the womb shall be called holy to the\nLord”),",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 13:2,12"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 2:24"},"and to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, “A pair of turtledoves, or two young\npigeons.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 12:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 2:25"},"Behold, there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon. This man was righteous and devout, looking for the\nconsolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was on him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 2:26"},"It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not see death before he had seen the Lord’s\nMasih.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Christ” (Greek) and “Messiah” (Hebrew) both mean “Anointed\nOne”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 2:27"},"He came in the Spirit into the temple. When the parents brought in the child, Isa, that they might do concerning him\naccording to the custom of the law, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 2:28"},"then he received him into his arms, and blessed Allah, and said,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 2:29"},"“Now you are releasing your servant, Master, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["according to your word, in peace; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 2:30"},"for my eyes have seen your salvation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 2:31"},"which you have prepared before the face of all peoples; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 2:32"},"a light for revelation to the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the glory of your people Israel.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 2:33"},"Yusuf and his mother were marvelling at the things which were spoken concerning him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 2:34"},"and Simeon blessed them, and said to Maryam, his mother, “Behold, this child is set for the falling and the rising of\nmany in Israel, and for a sign which is spoken against. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 2:35"},"Yes, a sword will pierce through your own soul, that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 2:36"},"There was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher (she was of a great age, having lived\nwith a husband seven years from her virginity, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 2:37"},"and she had been a widow for about eighty-four years), who didn’t depart from the temple, worshipping with fastings and\npetitions night and day. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 2:38"},"Coming up at that very hour, she gave thanks to the Lord, and spoke of him to all those who were looking for redemption\nin Jerusalem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 2:39"},"When they had accomplished all things that were according to the law of the Lord, they returned into Galilee, to their\nown city, Nazareth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 2:40"},"The child was growing, and was becoming strong in spirit, being filled with wisdom, and the grace of Allah was upon him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 2:41"},"His parents went every year to Jerusalem at the feast of the Passover.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 2:42"},"When he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem according to the custom of the feast,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 2:43"},"and when they had fulfilled the days, as they were returning, the boy Isa stayed behind in Jerusalem. Yusuf and his\nmother didn’t know it, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 2:44"},"but supposing him to be in the company, they went a day’s journey, and they looked for him amongst their relatives and\nacquaintances. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 2:45"},"When they didn’t find him, they returned to Jerusalem, looking for him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 2:46"},"After three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the middle of the teachers, both listening to them, and asking\nthem questions. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 2:47"},"All who heard him were amazed at his understanding and his answers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 2:48"},"When they saw him, they were astonished, and his mother said to him, “Son, why have you treated us this way? Behold, your\nfather and I were anxiously looking for you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 2:49"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why were you looking for me? Didn’t you know that I must be in my Father’s\nhouse?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 2:50"},"They didn’t understand the saying which he spoke to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 2:51"},"And he went down with them, and came to Nazareth. He was subject to them, and his mother kept all these sayings in her\nheart. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 2:52"},"And Isa increased in wisdom and stature, and in favour with Allah and men.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"LUK 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 3:1"},"Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor of Judea, and Herod being\ntetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of the region of Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias tetrarch of\nAbilene, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 3:2"},"in the high priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, the word of Allah came to Yahya, the son of Zacharias, in the wilderness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 3:3"},"He came into all the region around the Jordan, preaching the baptism of repentance for remission of sins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 3:4"},"As it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The voice of one crying in the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Make ready the way of the Lord. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Make his paths straight. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 3:5"},"Every valley will be filled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Every mountain and hill will be brought low. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The crooked will become straight, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the rough ways smooth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 3:6"},"All flesh will see Allah’s salvation.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["3:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah\n40:3-5"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 3:7"},"He said therefore to the multitudes who went out to be baptised by him, “You offspring of vipers, who warned you to flee\nfrom the wrath to come? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 3:8"},"Therefore produce fruits worthy of repentance, and don’t begin to say amongst yourselves, ‘We have Ibrahim for our\nfather;’ for I tell you that Allah is able to raise up children to Ibrahim from these stones!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 3:9"},"Even now the axe also lies at the root of the trees. Every tree therefore that doesn’t produce good fruit is cut down, and\nthrown into the fire.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 3:10"},"The multitudes asked him, “What then must we do?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 3:11"},"He answered them, “He who has two coats, let him give to him who has none. He who has food, let him do likewise.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 3:12"},"Tax collectors also came to be baptised, and they said to him, “Teacher, what must we do?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 3:13"},"He said to them, “Collect no more than that which is appointed to you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 3:14"},"Soldiers also asked him, saying, “What about us? What must we do?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to them, “Extort from no one by violence, neither accuse anyone wrongfully. Be content with your wages.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 3:15"},"As the people were in expectation, and all men reasoned in their hearts concerning Yahya, whether perhaps he was the\nMasih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 3:16"},"Yahya answered them all, “I indeed baptise you with water, but he comes who is mightier than I, the strap of whose\nsandals I am not worthy to loosen. He will baptise you in the Holy Spirit and fire,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 3:17"},"whose fan is in his hand, and he will thoroughly cleanse his threshing floor, and will gather the wheat into his barn;\nbut he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 3:18"},"Then with many other exhortations he preached good news to the people,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 3:19"},"but Herod the tetrarch,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["a tetrarch is one of four governors of a\nprovince"]}],"caller":"+"}," being reproved by him for Herodias, his brother’s ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “brother Philip’s” instead of “brother’s”"]}],"caller":"+"}," wife, and for all the evil things which Herod had done,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 3:20"},"added this also to them all, that he shut up Yahya in prison.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 3:21"},"Now when all the people were baptised, Isa also had been baptised, and was praying. The sky was opened,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 3:22"},"and the Holy Spirit descended in a bodily form like a dove on him; and a voice came out of the sky, saying “You are my\nbeloved Son. In you I am well pleased.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 3:23"},"Isa himself, when he began to teach, was about thirty years old, being the son (as was supposed) of Yusuf, the son of\nHeli, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 3:24"},"the son of Matthat, the son of Levi, the son of Melchi, the son of Jannai, the son of Yusuf,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 3:25"},"the son of Mattathias, the son of Amos, the son of Nahum, the son of Esli, the son of Naggai,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 3:26"},"the son of Maath, the son of Mattathias, the son of Semein, the son of Yusuf, the son of Judah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 3:27"},"the son of Joanan, the son of Rhesa, the son of Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, the son of Neri,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 3:28"},"the son of Melchi, the son of Addi, the son of Cosam, the son of Elmodam, the son of Er,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 3:29"},"the son of Jose, the son of Eliezer, the son of Jorim, the son of Matthat, the son of Levi,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 3:30"},"the son of Simeon, the son of Judah, the son of Yusuf, the son of Jonan, the son of Eliakim,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 3:31"},"the son of Melea, the son of Menan, the son of Mattatha, the son of Nathan, the son of Dawood,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 3:32"},"the son of Jesse, the son of Obed, the son of Boaz, the son of Salmon, the son of Nahshon,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 3:33"},"the son of Amminadab, the son of Aram,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU reads “Admin, the son of Arni” instead of\n“Aram”"]}],"caller":"+"}," the son of Hezron, the son of Perez, the son of Judah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 3:34"},"the son of Yaqub, the son of Isḥāq, the son of Ibrahim, the son of Terah, the son of Nahor,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 3:35"},"the son of Serug, the son of Reu, the son of Peleg, the son of Eber, the son of Shelah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 3:36"},"the son of Cainan, the son of Arphaxad, the son of Shem, the son of Nuh, the son of Lamech,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 3:37"},"the son of Methuselah, the son of Enoch, the son of Jared, the son of Mahalaleel, the son of Cainan,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 3:38"},"the son of Enos, the son of Seth, the son of Adam, the son of Allah.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"LUK 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 4:1"},"Isa, full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan, and was led by the Spirit into the wilderness\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 4:2"},"for forty days, being tempted by the Iblis. He ate nothing in those days. Afterward, when they were completed, he was\nhungry. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 4:3"},"The Iblis said to him, “If you are the Son of Allah, command this stone to become bread.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 4:4"},"Isa answered him, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is written, ‘Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word of\nAllah.’”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 8:3"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 4:5"},"The Iblis, leading him up on a high mountain, showed him all the kingdoms of the world in a moment of time.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 4:6"},"The Iblis said to him, “I will give you all this authority, and their glory, for it has been delivered to me; and I give\nit to whomever I want. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 4:7"},"If you therefore will worship before me, it will all be yours.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 4:8"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Get behind me Satan! For it is written, ‘You shall worship Allah your Lord, and you shall serve him\nonly.’”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:13"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 4:9"},"He led him to Jerusalem, and set him on the pinnacle of the temple, and said to him, “If you are the Son of Allah, cast\nyourself down from here, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 4:10"},"for it is written, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘He will put his angels in charge of you, to guard you;’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 4:11"},"and, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘On their hands they will bear you up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["lest perhaps you dash your foot against a stone.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:11\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 91:11-12 "]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 4:12"},"Isa answering, said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It has been said, ‘You shall not tempt Allah your\nLord.’”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:16"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 4:13"},"When the Iblis had completed every temptation, he departed from him until another time.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 4:14"},"Isa returned in the power of the Spirit into Galilee, and news about him spread through all the surrounding area.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 4:15"},"He taught in their synagogues, being glorified by all. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 4:16"},"He came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up. He entered, as was his custom, into the synagogue on the Sabbath day,\nand stood up to read. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 4:17"},"The book of the prophet Isaiah was handed to him. He opened the book, and found the place where it was written,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 4:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The Spirit of the Lord is on me,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["because he has anointed me to preach good news to the poor."]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He has sent me to heal the broken hearted,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:18\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits “to heal the broken hearted”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["to proclaim release to the captives,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["recovering of sight to the blind,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["to deliver those who are crushed,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 4:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and to proclaim the acceptable year of the Lord.”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 61:1-2"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 4:20"},"He closed the book, gave it back to the attendant, and sat down. The eyes of all in the synagogue were fastened on him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 4:21"},"He began to tell them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Today, this Scripture has been fulfilled in your\nhearing.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 4:22"},"All testified about him, and wondered at the gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth, and they said, “Isn’t this\nYusuf’s son?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 4:23"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Doubtless you will tell me this parable, ‘Physician, heal yourself! Whatever we have heard done at\nCapernaum, do also here in your hometown.’”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 4:24"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, no prophet is acceptable in his hometown.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 4:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But truly I tell you, there were many widows in Israel in the days of Ilyas, when the sky was shut up three years\nand six months, when a great famine came over all the land. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 4:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Ilyas was sent to none of them, except to Zarephath, in the land of Sidon, to a woman who was a widow.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 4:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["There were many lepers in Israel in the time of Alyas'a the prophet, yet not one of them was cleansed, except\nNaaman, the Syrian.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 4:28"},"They were all filled with wrath in the synagogue, as they heard these things.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 4:29"},"They rose up, threw him out of the city, and led him to the brow of the hill that their city was built on, that they\nmight throw him off the cliff. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 4:30"},"But he, passing through the middle of them, went his way. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 4:31"},"He came down to Capernaum, a city of Galilee. He was teaching them on the Sabbath day,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 4:32"},"and they were astonished at his teaching, for his word was with authority.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 4:33"},"In the synagogue there was a man who had a spirit of an unclean demon, and he cried out with a loud voice,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 4:34"},"saying, “Ah! what have we to do with you, Isa of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are: the Holy One\nof Allah!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 4:35"},"Isa rebuked him, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Be silent, and come out of him!”\n"]}," When the demon had thrown him down in the middle of them, he came out of him, having done him no harm.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 4:36"},"Amazement came on all, and they spoke together, one with another, saying, “What is this word? For with authority and\npower he commands the unclean spirits, and they come out!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 4:37"},"News about him went out into every place of the surrounding region.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 4:38"},"He rose up from the synagogue, and entered into Shima’un’s house. Shima’un’s mother-in-law was afflicted with a great\nfever, and they begged him for her. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 4:39"},"He stood over her, and rebuked the fever; and it left her. Immediately she rose up and served them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 4:40"},"When the sun was setting, all those who had any sick with various diseases brought them to him; and he laid his hands on\nevery one of them, and healed them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 4:41"},"Demons also came out of many, crying out, and saying, “You are the Masih, the Son of Allah!” Rebuking them, he didn’t\nallow them to speak, because they knew that he was the Masih. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 4:42"},"When it was day, he departed and went into an uninhabited place, and the multitudes looked for him, and came to him, and\nheld on to him, so that he wouldn’t go away from them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 4:43"},"But he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I must preach the good news of Allah’s Kingdom to the other cities also. For this reason I have\nbeen sent.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 4:44"},"He was preaching in the synagogues of Galilee. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"LUK 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 5:1"},"Now while the multitude pressed on him and heard the word of Allah, he was standing by the lake of Gennesaret.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 5:2"},"He saw two boats standing by the lake, but the fishermen had gone out of them, and were washing their nets.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 5:3"},"He entered into one of the boats, which was Shima’un’s, and asked him to put out a little from the land. He sat down and\ntaught the multitudes from the boat. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 5:4"},"When he had finished speaking, he said to Shima’un, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Put out into the deep, and let down your nets for a\ncatch.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 5:5"},"Shima’un answered him, “Master, we worked all night, and took nothing; but at your word I will let down the net.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 5:6"},"When they had done this, they caught a great multitude of fish, and their net was breaking.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 5:7"},"They beckoned to their partners in the other boat, that they should come and help them. They came, and filled both boats,\nso that they began to sink. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 5:8"},"But Shima’un Peter, when he saw it, fell down at Isa’s knees, saying, “Depart from me, for I am a sinful man, Lord.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 5:9"},"For he was amazed, and all who were with him, at the catch of fish which they had caught;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 5:10"},"and so also were Yaqub and Yuhanna, sons of Zebedee, who were partners with Shima’un.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Isa said to Shima’un, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t be afraid. From now on you will be catching people\nalive.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 5:11"},"When they had brought their boats to land, they left everything, and followed him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 5:12"},"While he was in one of the cities, behold, there was a man full of leprosy. When he saw Isa, he fell on his face, and\nbegged him, saying, “Lord, if you want to, you can make me clean.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 5:13"},"He stretched out his hand, and touched him, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I want to. Be made\nclean.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Immediately the leprosy left him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 5:14"},"He commanded him to tell no one, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But go your way, and show yourself to the priest, and offer for your cleansing\naccording to what Musa commanded, for a testimony to them.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 5:15"},"But the report concerning him spread much more, and great multitudes came together to hear, and to be healed by him of\ntheir infirmities. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 5:16"},"But he withdrew himself into the desert, and prayed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 5:17"},"On one of those days, he was teaching; and there were Pharisees and teachers of the law sitting by, who had come out of\nevery village of Galilee, Judea, and Jerusalem. The power of the Lord was with him to heal them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 5:18"},"Behold, men brought a paralysed man on a cot, and they sought to bring him in to lay before Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 5:19"},"Not finding a way to bring him in because of the multitude, they went up to the housetop, and let him down through the\ntiles with his cot into the middle before Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 5:20"},"Seeing their faith, he said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Man, your sins are forgiven\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 5:21"},"The scribes and the Pharisees began to reason, saying, “Who is this that speaks blasphemies? Who can forgive sins, but\nAllah alone?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 5:22"},"But Isa, perceiving their thoughts, answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why are you reasoning so in your hearts?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 5:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Which is easier to say, ‘Your sins are forgiven you;’ or to say, ‘Arise and walk?’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 5:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive\nsins”"]}," (he said to the paralysed man), ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, arise, take up your cot, and go to your\nhouse.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 5:25"},"Immediately he rose up before them, and took up that which he was laying on, and departed to his house, glorifying Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 5:26"},"Amazement took hold on all, and they glorified Allah. They were filled with fear, saying, “We have seen strange things\ntoday.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 5:27"},"After these things he went out, and saw a tax collector named Levi sitting at the tax office, and said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Follow me!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 5:28"},"He left everything, and rose up and followed him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 5:29"},"Levi made a great feast for him in his house. There was a great crowd of tax collectors and others who were reclining\nwith them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 5:30"},"Their scribes and the Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, “Why do you eat and drink with the tax collectors\nand sinners?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 5:31"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Those who are healthy have no need for a physician, but those who are sick do.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 5:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I have not come to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 5:33"},"They said to him, “Why do Yahya’s disciples often fast and pray, likewise also the disciples of the Pharisees, but yours\neat and drink?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 5:34"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Can you make the friends of the bridegroom fast while the bridegroom is with them?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 5:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the days will come when the bridegroom will be taken away from them. Then they will fast in those\ndays.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 5:36"},"He also told a parable to them. ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“No one puts a piece from a new garment on an old garment, or else he will tear the\nnew, and also the piece from the new will not match the old. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 5:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No one puts new wine into old wine skins, or else the new wine will burst the skins, and it will be spilled, and the\nskins will be destroyed. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 5:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But new wine must be put into fresh wine skins, and both are preserved.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 5:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No man having drunk old wine immediately desires new, for he says, ‘The old is\nbetter.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"LUK 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 6:1"},"Now on the second Sabbath after the first, he was going through the grain fields. His disciples plucked the heads of grain\nand ate, rubbing them in their hands. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 6:2"},"But some of the Pharisees said to them, “Why do you do that which is not lawful to do on the Sabbath day?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 6:3"},"Isa, answering them, said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Haven’t you read what Dawood did when he was hungry, he, and those who were with him;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 6:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["how he entered into Allah’s house, and took and ate the show bread, and gave also to those who were with him, which\nis not lawful to eat except for the priests alone?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 6:5"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The Son of Man is lord of the Sabbath.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 6:6"},"It also happened on another Sabbath that he entered into the synagogue and taught. There was a man there, and his right\nhand was withered. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 6:7"},"The scribes and the Pharisees watched him, to see whether he would heal on the Sabbath, that they might find an accusation\nagainst him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 6:8"},"But he knew their thoughts; and he said to the man who had the withered hand,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Rise up, and stand in the middle.”"]}," He arose and stood. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 6:9"},"Then Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I will ask you something: Is it lawful on the Sabbath to do good, or to do harm? To save a\nlife, or to kill?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 6:10"},"He looked around at them all, and said to the man, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Stretch out your\nhand.”"]}," He did, and his hand was restored as sound as the other.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 6:11"},"But they were filled with rage, and talked with one another about what they might do to Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 6:12"},"In these days, he went out to the mountain to pray, and he continued all night in prayer to Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 6:13"},"When it was day, he called his disciples, and from them he chose twelve, whom he also named apostles:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 6:14"},"Shima’un, whom he also named Peter; Andreas, his brother; Yaqub; Yuhanna; Philip; Bar-Talmai;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 6:15"},"Matti; Tau’ma; Yaqub, the son of Alphaeus; Shima’un, who was called the Zealot;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 6:16"},"Yehuda the son of Yaqub; and Yehuda Iscariot, who also became a traitor.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 6:17"},"He came down with them, and stood on a level place, with a crowd of his disciples, and a great number of the people from\nall Judea and Jerusalem, and the sea coast of Tyre and Sidon, who came to hear him and to be healed of their diseases;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 6:18"},"as well as those who were troubled by unclean spirits, and they were being healed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 6:19"},"All the multitude sought to touch him, for power came out of him and healed them all.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 6:20"},"He lifted up his eyes to his disciples, and said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Blessed are you who are poor,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Allah’s Kingdom is yours."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 6:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed are you who hunger now,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for you will be filled."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed are you who weep now,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for you will laugh."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 6:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed are you when men hate you, and when they exclude and mock you, and throw out your name as evil, for the Son\nof Man’s sake. "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 6:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Rejoice in that day, and leap for joy, for behold, your reward is great in heaven, for their fathers did the same\nthing to the prophets."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 6:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But woe to you who are rich!"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For you have received your consolation."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 6:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you, you who are full now,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for you will be hungry."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you who laugh now,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for you will mourn and weep."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 6:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “to you”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["when"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “all” "]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["men speak well of you,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for their fathers did the same thing to the false prophets."]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 6:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But I tell you who hear: love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 6:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["bless those who curse you, and pray for those who mistreat you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 6:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["To him who strikes you on the cheek, offer also the other; and from him who takes away your cloak, don’t withhold\nyour coat also. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 6:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Give to everyone who asks you, and don’t ask him who takes away your goods to give them back\nagain."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 6:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“As you would like people to do to you, do exactly so to them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 6:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you love those who love you, what credit is that to you? For even sinners love those who love them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 6:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you do good to those who do good to you, what credit is that to you? For even sinners do the same.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 6:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you lend to those from whom you hope to receive, what credit is that to you? Even sinners lend to sinners, to\nreceive back as much. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 6:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing back; and your reward will be great, and you will be\nchildren of the Most High; for he is kind towards the unthankful and\nevil."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 6:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Therefore be merciful,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["even as your Father is also merciful."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 6:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t judge,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and you won’t be judged."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t condemn,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and you won’t be condemned."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Set free,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and you will be set free."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 6:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Give, and it will be given to you: good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over, will be given to\nyou."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, into your bosom."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For with the same measure you measure it will be measured back to\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 6:39"},"He spoke a parable to them. ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Can the blind guide the blind? Won’t they both fall into a pit?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 6:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A disciple is not above his teacher, but everyone when he is fully trained will be like his teacher.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 6:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Why do you see the speck of chaff that is in your brother’s eye, but don’t consider the beam that is in your own\neye? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 6:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or how can you tell your brother, ‘Brother, let me remove the speck of chaff that is in your eye,’ when you yourself\ndon’t see the beam that is in your own eye? You hypocrite! First remove the beam from your own eye, and then you can see\nclearly to remove the speck of chaff that is in your brother’s eye.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 6:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For there is no good tree that produces rotten fruit; nor again a rotten tree that produces good fruit.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 6:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For each tree is known by its own fruit. For people don’t gather figs from thorns, nor do they gather grapes from a\nbramble bush. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 6:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The good man out of the good treasure of his heart brings out that which is good, and the evil man out of the evil\ntreasure of his heart brings out that which is evil, for out of the abundance of the heart, his mouth\nspeaks."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 6:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why do you call me, ‘Lord, Lord,’ and don’t do the things which I say?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 6:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Everyone who comes to me, and hears my words, and does them, I will show you who he is like.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 6:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He is like a man building a house, who dug and went deep, and laid a foundation on the rock. When a flood arose, the\nstream broke against that house, and could not shake it, because it was founded on the rock.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 6:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But he who hears, and doesn’t do, is like a man who built a house on the earth without a foundation, against which\nthe stream broke, and immediately it fell, and the ruin of that house was\ngreat.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"LUK 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 7:1"},"After he had finished speaking in the hearing of the people, he entered into Capernaum.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 7:2"},"A certain centurion’s servant, who was dear to him, was sick and at the point of death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 7:3"},"When he heard about Isa, he sent to him elders of the Jews, asking him to come and save his servant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 7:4"},"When they came to Isa, they begged him earnestly, saying, “He is worthy for you to do this for him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 7:5"},"for he loves our nation, and he built our synagogue for us.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 7:6"},"Isa went with them. When he was now not far from the house, the centurion sent friends to him, saying to him, “Lord, don’t\ntrouble yourself, for I am not worthy for you to come under my roof.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 7:7"},"Therefore I didn’t even think myself worthy to come to you; but say the word, and my servant will be healed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 7:8"},"For I also am a man placed under authority, having under myself soldiers. I tell this one, ‘Go!’ and he goes; and to\nanother, ‘Come!’ and he comes; and to my servant, ‘Do this,’ and he does it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 7:9"},"When Isa heard these things, he marvelled at him, and turned and said to the multitude who followed him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, I have not found such great faith, no, not in Israel.”"]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 7:10"},"Those who were sent, returning to the house, found that the servant who had been sick was well.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 7:11"},"Soon afterwards, he went to a city called Nain. Many of his disciples, along with a great multitude, went with him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 7:12"},"Now when he came near to the gate of the city, behold, one who was dead was carried out, the only son of his mother, and\nshe was a widow. Many people of the city were with her. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 7:13"},"When the Lord saw her, he had compassion on her, and said to her,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t cry.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 7:14"},"He came near and touched the coffin, and the bearers stood still. He said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Young man, I tell you, arise!”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 7:15"},"He who was dead sat up, and began to speak. And he gave him to his mother.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 7:16"},"Fear took hold of all, and they glorified Allah, saying, “A great prophet has arisen amongst us!” and, “Allah has visited\nhis people!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 7:17"},"This report went out concerning him in the whole of Judea, and in all the surrounding region.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 7:18"},"The disciples of Yahya told him about all these things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 7:19"},"Yahya, calling to himself two of his disciples, sent them to Isa, saying, “Are you the one who is coming, or should we\nlook for another?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 7:20"},"When the men had come to him, they said, “Yahya the Baptiser has sent us to you, saying, ‘Are you he who comes, or should\nwe look for another?’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 7:21"},"In that hour he cured many of diseases and plagues and evil spirits; and to many who were blind he gave sight.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 7:22"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go and tell Yahya the things which you have seen and heard: that the blind receive their sight,\nthe lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised up, and the poor have good news preached to them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 7:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed is he who finds no occasion for stumbling in me.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 7:24"},"When Yahya’s messengers had departed, he began to tell the multitudes about Yuhanna,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 7:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But what did you go out to see? A man clothed in soft clothing? Behold, those who are gorgeously dressed, and live\ndelicately, are in kings’ courts. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 7:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But what did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and much more than a prophet.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 7:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["This is he of whom it is written,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Behold, I send my messenger before your face,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["who will prepare your way before you.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:27\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Malachi 3:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 7:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“For I tell you, amongst those who are born of women there is not a greater prophet than Yahya the Baptiser, yet he\nwho is least in Allah’s Kingdom is greater than he.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 7:29"},"When all the people and the tax collectors heard this, they declared Allah to be just, having been baptised with Yahya’s\nbaptism. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 7:30"},"But the Pharisees and the lawyers rejected the counsel of Allah, not being baptised by him themselves.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 7:31"},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “But the Lord said,”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To what then should I compare the people of this generation?\nWhat are they like? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 7:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They are like children who sit in the marketplace, and call to one another, saying, ‘We piped to you, and you didn’t\ndance. We mourned, and you didn’t weep.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 7:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For Yahya the Baptiser came neither eating bread nor drinking wine, and you say, ‘He has a demon.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 7:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The Son of Man has come eating and drinking, and you say, ‘Behold, a gluttonous man, and a drunkard; a friend of tax\ncollectors and sinners!’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 7:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Wisdom is justified by all her children.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 7:36"},"One of the Pharisees invited him to eat with him. He entered into the Pharisee’s house, and sat at the table.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 7:37"},"Behold, a woman in the city who was a sinner, when she knew that he was reclining in the Pharisee’s house, brought an\nalabaster jar of ointment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 7:38"},"Standing behind at his feet weeping, she began to wet his feet with her tears, and she wiped them with the hair of her\nhead, kissed his feet, and anointed them with the ointment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 7:39"},"Now when the Pharisee who had invited him saw it, he said to himself, “This man, if he were a prophet, would have\nperceived who and what kind of woman this is who touches him, that she is a sinner.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 7:40"},"Isa answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Shima’un, I have something to tell you.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Teacher, say on.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 7:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain lender had two debtors. The one owed five hundred denarii, and the other fifty.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 7:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When they couldn’t pay, he forgave them both. Which of them therefore will love him\nmost?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 7:43"},"Shima’un answered, “He, I suppose, to whom he forgave the most.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You have judged correctly.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 7:44"},"Turning to the woman, he said to Shima’un, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you see this woman? I entered into your house, and you gave me no\nwater for my feet, but she has wet my feet with her tears, and wiped them with the hair of her head.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 7:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You gave me no kiss, but she, since the time I came in, has not ceased to kiss my feet.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 7:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You didn’t anoint my head with oil, but she has anointed my feet with ointment.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 7:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore I tell you, her sins, which are many, are forgiven, for she loved much. But one to whom little is\nforgiven, loves little.” "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 7:48"},"He said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Your sins are forgiven.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 7:49"},"Those who sat at the table with him began to say to themselves, “Who is this who even forgives sins?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 7:50"},"He said to the woman, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Your faith has saved you. Go in peace.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"LUK 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 8:1"},"Soon afterwards, he went about through cities and villages, preaching and bringing the good news of Allah’s Kingdom. With\nhim were the twelve, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 8:2"},"and certain women who had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities: Maryam who was called Magdalene, from whom seven\ndemons had gone out; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 8:3"},"and Joanna, the wife of Chuzas, Herod’s steward; Susanna; and many others; who served\nthem",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “him” instead of “them”"]}],"caller":"+"}," from their possessions.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 8:4"},"When a great multitude came together, and people from every city were coming to him, he spoke by a parable.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 8:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The farmer went out to sow his seed. As he sowed, some fell along the road, and it was trampled under foot, and the\nbirds of the sky devoured it. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 8:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Other seed fell on the rock, and as soon as it grew, it withered away, because it had no moisture.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 8:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Other fell amid the thorns, and the thorns grew with it, and choked it.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 8:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Other fell into the good ground, and grew, and produced one hundred times as much\nfruit.”"]}," As he said these things, he called out, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He who has ears to hear, let him\nhear!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 8:9"},"Then his disciples asked him, “What does this parable mean?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 8:10"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To you it is given to know the mysteries of Allah’s Kingdom, but to the rest in parables; that ‘seeing they\nmay not see, and hearing they may not understand.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:10\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 6:9"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 8:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now the parable is this: The seed is the word of Allah.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 8:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Those along the road are those who hear, then the Iblis comes, and takes away the word from their heart, that they\nmay not believe and be saved. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 8:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Those on the rock are they who, when they hear, receive the word with joy; but these have no root, who believe for a\nwhile, then fall away in time of temptation. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 8:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["That which fell amongst the thorns, these are those who have heard, and as they go on their way they are choked with\ncares, riches, and pleasures of life, and bring no fruit to maturity.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 8:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Those in the good ground, these are those who with an honest and good heart, having heard the word, hold it tightly,\nand produce fruit with perseverance."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 8:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“No one, when he has lit a lamp, covers it with a container, or puts it under a bed; but puts it on a stand, that\nthose who enter in may see the light. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 8:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For nothing is hidden that will not be revealed; nor anything secret that will not be known and come to light.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 8:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Be careful therefore how you hear. For whoever has, to him will be given; and whoever doesn’t have, from him will be\ntaken away even that which he thinks he has.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 8:19"},"His mother and brothers came to him, and they could not come near him for the crowd.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 8:20"},"Some people told him, “Your mother and your brothers stand outside, desiring to see you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 8:21"},"But he answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My mother and my brothers are these who hear the word of Allah, and do\nit.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 8:22"},"Now on one of those days, he entered into a boat, himself and his disciples, and he said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Let’s go over to the other side of the lake.”"]}," So they launched out.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 8:23"},"But as they sailed, he fell asleep. A wind storm came down on the lake, and they were taking on dangerous amounts of\nwater. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 8:24"},"They came to him, and awoke him, saying, “Master, master, we are dying!” He awoke, and rebuked the wind and the raging of\nthe water, and they ceased, and it was calm.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["See\nZabur 107:29"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 8:25"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Where is your faith?”"]}," Being afraid they marvelled, saying to one another, “Who is this then,\nthat he commands even the winds and the water, and they obey him?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 8:26"},"They arrived at the country of the Gadarenes, which is opposite Galilee.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 8:27"},"When Isa stepped ashore, a certain man out of the city who had demons for a long time met him. He wore no clothes, and\ndidn’t live in a house, but in the tombs. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 8:28"},"When he saw Isa, he cried out, and fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, “What do I have to do with you, Isa,\nyou Son of the Most High Allah? I beg you, don’t torment me!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 8:29"},"For Isa was commanding the unclean spirit to come out of the man. For the unclean spirit had often seized the man. He was\nkept under guard, and bound with chains and fetters. Breaking the bonds apart, he was driven by the demon into the desert.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 8:30"},"Isa asked him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What is your name?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Legion,” for many demons had entered into him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 8:31"},"They begged him that he would not command them to go into the abyss.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 8:32"},"Now there was there a herd of many pigs feeding on the mountain, and they begged him that he would allow them to enter\ninto those. Then he allowed them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 8:33"},"The demons came out of the man, and entered into the pigs, and the herd rushed down the steep bank into the lake, and\nwere drowned. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 8:34"},"When those who fed them saw what had happened, they fled and told it in the city and in the country.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 8:35"},"People went out to see what had happened. They came to Isa and found the man from whom the demons had gone out, sitting\nat Isa’s feet, clothed and in his right mind; and they were afraid.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 8:36"},"Those who saw it told them how he who had been possessed by demons was healed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 8:37"},"All the people of the surrounding country of the Gadarenes asked him to depart from them, for they were very much afraid.\nThen he entered into the boat and returned. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 8:38"},"But the man from whom the demons had gone out begged him that he might go with him, but Isa sent him away, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 8:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Return to your house, and declare what great things Allah has done for\nyou.”"]}," He went his way, proclaiming throughout the whole city what great things Isa had done for him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 8:40"},"When Isa returned, the multitude welcomed him, for they were all waiting for him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 8:41"},"Behold, a man named Jairus came. He was a ruler of the synagogue. He fell down at Isa’s feet, and begged him to come into\nhis house, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 8:42"},"for he had an only daughter, about twelve years of age, and she was dying. But as he went, the multitudes pressed against\nhim. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 8:43"},"A woman who had a flow of blood for twelve years, who had spent all her living on physicians and could not be healed by\nany \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 8:44"},"came behind him, and touched the fringe",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or,\ntassel"]}],"caller":"+"}," of his cloak. Immediately the flow of her blood stopped.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 8:45"},"Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Who touched me?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When all denied it, Peter and those with him said, “Master, the multitudes press and jostle you, and you say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Who touched me?’"]},"” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 8:46"},"But Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Someone did touch me, for I perceived that power has gone out of\nme.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 8:47"},"When the woman saw that she was not hidden, she came trembling, and falling down before him declared to him in the\npresence of all the people the reason why she had touched him, and how she was healed immediately.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 8:48"},"He said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Daughter, cheer up. Your faith has made you well. Go in\npeace.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 8:49"},"While he still spoke, one from the ruler of the synagogue’s house came, saying to him, “Your daughter is dead. Don’t\ntrouble the Teacher.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 8:50"},"But Isa hearing it, answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t be afraid. Only believe, and she will be\nhealed.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 8:51"},"When he came to the house, he didn’t allow anyone to enter in, except Peter, Yuhanna, Yaqub, the father of the child, and\nher mother. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 8:52"},"All were weeping and mourning her, but he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t weep. She isn’t dead, but\nsleeping.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 8:53"},"They were ridiculing him, knowing that she was dead. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 8:54"},"But he put them all outside, and taking her by the hand, he called, saying,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Child, arise!”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 8:55"},"Her spirit returned, and she rose up immediately. He commanded that something be given to her to eat.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 8:56"},"Her parents were amazed, but he commanded them to tell no one what had been done.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"LUK 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 9:1"},"He called the twelve",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “his twelve disciples” instead of “the\ntwelve”"]}],"caller":"+"}," together, and gave them power and authority over all demons, and to cure diseases.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 9:2"},"He sent them out to preach Allah’s Kingdom and to heal the sick.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 9:3"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Take nothing for your journey—no staffs, nor wallet, nor bread, nor money. Don’t have two coats\neach. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 9:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Into whatever house you enter, stay there, and depart from there.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 9:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As many as don’t receive you, when you depart from that city, shake off even the dust from your feet for a testimony\nagainst them.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 9:6"},"They departed and went throughout the villages, preaching the Good News and healing everywhere.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 9:7"},"Now Herod the tetrarch heard of all that was done by him; and he was very perplexed, because it was said by some that\nYahya had risen from the dead, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 9:8"},"and by some that Ilyas had appeared, and by others that one of the old prophets had risen again.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 9:9"},"Herod said, “I beheaded Yahya, but who is this about whom I hear such things?” He sought to see him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 9:10"},"The apostles, when they had returned, told him what things they had done.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He took them and withdrew apart to a desert region of",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:10\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits “a desert region of”."]}],"caller":"+"}," a city called Bethsaida. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 9:11"},"But the multitudes, perceiving it, followed him. He welcomed them, spoke to them of Allah’s Kingdom, and he cured those\nwho needed healing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 9:12"},"The day began to wear away; and the twelve came and said to him, “Send the multitude away, that they may go into the\nsurrounding villages and farms, and lodge, and get food, for we are here in a deserted place.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 9:13"},"But he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You give them something to eat.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said, “We have no more than five loaves and two fish, unless we should go and buy food for all these people.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 9:14"},"For they were about five thousand men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to his disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Make them sit down in groups of about fifty\neach.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 9:15"},"They did so, and made them all sit down. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 9:16"},"He took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to the sky, he blessed them, broke them, and gave them to the\ndisciples to set before the multitude. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 9:17"},"They ate and were all filled. They gathered up twelve baskets of broken pieces that were left over.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 9:18"},"As he was praying alone, the disciples were with him, and he asked them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Who do the multitudes say that I am?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 9:19"},"They answered, “‘Yahya the Baptiser,’ but others say, ‘Ilyas,’ and others, that one of the old prophets has risen again.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 9:20"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But who do you say that I am?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Peter answered, “The Masih of Allah.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 9:21"},"But he warned them, and commanded them to tell this to no one,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 9:22"},"saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The Son of Man must suffer many things, and be rejected by the elders, chief priests, and scribes, and be\nkilled, and the third day be raised up.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 9:23"},"He said to all, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If anyone desires to come after me, let him deny himself, take up his\ncross,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR, NU add “daily”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and follow me.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 9:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For whoever desires to save his life will lose it, but whoever will lose his life for my sake, will save it.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 9:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For what does it profit a man if he gains the whole world, and loses or forfeits his own self?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 9:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For whoever will be ashamed of me and of my words, of him will the Son of Man be ashamed, when he comes in his\nglory, and the glory of the Father, and of the holy angels. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 9:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I tell you the truth: There are some of those who stand here who will in no way taste of death until they see\nAllah’s Kingdom.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 9:28"},"About eight days after these sayings, he took with him Peter, Yuhanna, and Yaqub, and went up onto the mountain to pray.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 9:29"},"As he was praying, the appearance of his face was altered, and his clothing became white and dazzling.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 9:30"},"Behold, two men were talking with him, who were Musa and Ilyas,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 9:31"},"who appeared in glory, and spoke of his departure,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:31\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, “exodus”"]}],"caller":"+"}," which he was about to accomplish at Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 9:32"},"Now Peter and those who were with him were heavy with sleep, but when they were fully awake, they saw his glory, and the\ntwo men who stood with him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 9:33"},"As they were parting from him, Peter said to Isa, “Master, it is good for us to be here. Let’s make three tents: one for\nyou, one for Musa, and one for Ilyas,” not knowing what he said.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 9:34"},"While he said these things, a cloud came and overshadowed them, and they were afraid as they entered into the cloud.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 9:35"},"A voice came out of the cloud, saying, “This is my beloved Son. Listen to him!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 9:36"},"When the voice came, Isa was found alone. They were silent, and told no one in those days any of the things which they\nhad seen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 9:37"},"On the next day, when they had come down from the mountain, a great multitude met him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 9:38"},"Behold, a man from the crowd called out, saying, “Teacher, I beg you to look at my son, for he is my only child.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 9:39"},"Behold, a spirit takes him, he suddenly cries out, and it convulses him so that he foams, and it hardly departs from him,\nbruising him severely. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 9:40"},"I begged your disciples to cast it out, and they couldn’t.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 9:41"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you and bear with you? Bring your son\nhere.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 9:42"},"While he was still coming, the demon threw him down and convulsed him violently. But Isa rebuked the unclean spirit,\nhealed the boy, and gave him back to his father. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 9:43"},"They were all astonished at the majesty of Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But while all were marvelling at all the things which Isa did, he said to his disciples,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 9:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Let these words sink into your ears, for the Son of Man will be delivered up into the hands of\nmen.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 9:45"},"But they didn’t understand this saying. It was concealed from them, that they should not perceive it, and they were\nafraid to ask him about this saying. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 9:46"},"An argument arose amongst them about which of them was the greatest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 9:47"},"Isa, perceiving the reasoning of their hearts, took a little child, and set him by his side,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 9:48"},"and said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Whoever receives this little child in my name receives me. Whoever receives me receives him who\nsent me. For whoever is least amongst you all, this one will be great.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 9:49"},"Yuhanna answered, “Master, we saw someone casting out demons in your name, and we forbade him, because he doesn’t follow\nwith us.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 9:50"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Don’t forbid him, for he who is not against us is for\nus.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 9:51"},"It came to pass, when the days were near that he should be taken up, he intently set his face to go to Jerusalem\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 9:52"},"and sent messengers before his face. They went and entered into a village of the Samaritans, so as to prepare for him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 9:53"},"They didn’t receive him, because he was travelling with his face set towards Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 9:54"},"When his disciples, Yaqub and Yuhanna, saw this, they said, “Lord, do you want us to command fire to come down from the\nsky, and destroy them, just as Ilyas did?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 9:55"},"But he turned and rebuked them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You don’t know of what kind of spirit you are.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 9:56"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the Son of Man didn’t come to destroy men’s lives, but to save\nthem.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They went to another village. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"LUK 9:57"},"As they went on the way, a certain man said to him, “I want to follow you wherever you go, Lord.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"LUK 9:58"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The foxes have holes, and the birds of the sky have nests, but the Son of Man has no place to lay\nhis head.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"LUK 9:59"},"He said to another, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Follow me!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But he said, “Lord, allow me first to go and bury my father.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"LUK 9:60"},"But Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Leave the dead to bury their own dead, but you go and announce Allah’s\nKingdom.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"LUK 9:61"},"Another also said, “I want to follow you, Lord, but first allow me to say good-bye to those who are at my house.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"LUK 9:62"},"But Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“No one, having put his hand to the plough, and looking back, is fit for Allah’s\nKingdom.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"LUK 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 10:1"},"Now after these things, the Lord also appointed seventy others, and sent them two by two ahead of\nhim",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, “before his face”"]}],"caller":"+"}," into every city and place where he was about to come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 10:2"},"Then he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The harvest is indeed plentiful, but the labourers are few. Pray therefore to the Lord of the\nharvest, that he may send out labourers into his harvest. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 10:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Go your ways. Behold, I send you out as lambs amongst wolves.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 10:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Carry no purse, nor wallet, nor sandals. Greet no one on the way.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 10:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Into whatever house you enter, first say, ‘Peace be to this house.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 10:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If a son of peace is there, your peace will rest on him; but if not, it will return to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 10:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remain in that same house, eating and drinking the things they give, for the labourer is worthy of his wages. Don’t\ngo from house to house. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 10:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Into whatever city you enter, and they receive you, eat the things that are set before you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 10:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Heal the sick who are there, and tell them, ‘Allah’s Kingdom has come near to you.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 10:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But into whatever city you enter, and they don’t receive you, go out into its streets and say,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 10:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Even the dust from your city that clings to us, we wipe off against you. Nevertheless know this, that Allah’s\nKingdom has come near to you.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 10:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, it will be more tolerable in that day for Sodom than for that\ncity."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 10:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon which were\ndone in you, they would have repented long ago, sitting in sackcloth and ashes.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 10:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But it will be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon in the judgement than for you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 10:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You, Capernaum, who are exalted to heaven, will be brought down to Hades.\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hades is the lower realm of the dead, or\nHell."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 10:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whoever listens to you listens to me, and whoever rejects you rejects me. Whoever rejects me rejects him who sent\nme.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 10:17"},"The seventy returned with joy, saying, “Lord, even the demons are subject to us in your name!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 10:18"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I saw Iblis having fallen like lightning from heaven.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 10:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, I give you authority to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy. Nothing will\nin any way hurt you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 10:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Nevertheless, don’t rejoice in this, that the spirits are subject to you, but rejoice that your names are written in\nheaven.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 10:21"},"In that same hour Isa rejoiced in the Holy Spirit, and said,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I thank you, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you have hidden these things from the wise and understanding, and\nrevealed them to little children. Yes, Father, for so it was well-pleasing in your\nsight.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 10:22"},"Turning to the disciples, he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“All things have been delivered to me by my Father. No one knows who the Son is,\nexcept the Father, and who the Father is, except the Son, and he to whomever the Son desires to reveal\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 10:23"},"Turning to the disciples, he said privately, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Blessed are the eyes which see the things that you see,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 10:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I tell you that many prophets and kings desired to see the things which you see, and didn’t see them, and to\nhear the things which you hear, and didn’t hear them.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 10:25"},"Behold, a certain lawyer stood up and tested him, saying, “Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 10:26"},"He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What is written in the law? How do you read it?”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 10:27"},"He answered, “You shall love Allah your Lord with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your strength, and with\nall your mind;",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:5"]}],"caller":"+"}," and your neighbour as\nyourself.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:27 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 19:18"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 10:28"},"He said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You have answered correctly. Do this, and you will\nlive.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 10:29"},"But he, desiring to justify himself, asked Isa, “Who is my neighbour?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 10:30"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and he fell amongst robbers, who both stripped\nhim and beat him, and departed, leaving him half dead. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 10:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["By chance a certain priest was going down that way. When he saw him, he passed by on the other side.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 10:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In the same way a Levite also, when he came to the place, and saw him, passed by on the other side.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 10:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But a certain Samaritan, as he travelled, came where he was. When he saw him, he was moved with compassion,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 10:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["came to him, and bound up his wounds, pouring on oil and wine. He set him on his own animal, brought him to an inn,\nand took care of him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 10:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["On the next day, when he departed, he took out two denarii, gave them to the host, and said to him, ‘Take care of\nhim. Whatever you spend beyond that, I will repay you when I return.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 10:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now which of these three do you think seemed to be a neighbour to him who fell amongst the\nrobbers?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 10:37"},"He said, “He who showed mercy on him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go and do likewise.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 10:38"},"As they went on their way, he entered into a certain village, and a certain woman named Martha received him into her\nhouse. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 10:39"},"She had a sister called Maryam, who also sat at Isa’s feet, and heard his word.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 10:40"},"But Martha was distracted with much serving, and she came up to him, and said, “Lord, don’t you care that my sister left\nme to serve alone? Ask her therefore to help me.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 10:41"},"Isa answered her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Martha, Martha, you are anxious and troubled about many things,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 10:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but one thing is needed. Maryam has chosen the good part, which will not be taken away from\nher.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"LUK 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 11:1"},"When he finished praying in a certain place, one of his disciples said to him, “Lord, teach us to pray, just as Yahya also\ntaught his disciples.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 11:2"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When you pray, say,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘Our Father in heaven,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["may your name be kept holy."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["May your Kingdom come."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["May your will be done on earth, as it is in heaven."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 11:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Give us day by day our daily bread."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 11:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Forgive us our sins,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for we ourselves also forgive everyone who is indebted to us.\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Bring us not into temptation,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but deliver us from the evil one.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 11:5"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Which of you, if you go to a friend at midnight, and tell him, ‘Friend, lend me three loaves of\nbread, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 11:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for a friend of mine has come to me from a journey, and I have nothing to set before him,’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 11:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and he from within will answer and say, ‘Don’t bother me. The door is now shut, and my children are with me in bed. I\ncan’t get up and give it to you’? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 11:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, although he will not rise and give it to him because he is his friend, yet because of his persistence, he\nwill get up and give him as many as he needs."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 11:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, keep asking, and it will be given you. Keep seeking, and you will find. Keep knocking, and it will be\nopened to you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 11:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For everyone who asks receives. He who seeks finds. To him who knocks it will be\nopened."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 11:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Which of you fathers, if your son asks for bread, will give him a stone? Or if he asks for a fish, he won’t give\nhim a snake instead of a fish, will he? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 11:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or if he asks for an egg, he won’t give him a scorpion, will he?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 11:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your heavenly Father give\nthe Holy Spirit to those who ask him?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 11:14"},"He was casting out a demon, and it was mute. When the demon had gone out, the mute man spoke; and the multitudes\nmarvelled. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 11:15"},"But some of them said, “He casts out demons by Beelzebul, the prince of the demons.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 11:16"},"Others, testing him, sought from him a sign from heaven. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 11:17"},"But he, knowing their thoughts, said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation. A house\ndivided against itself falls. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 11:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If Iblis also is divided against himself, how will his kingdom stand? For you say that I cast out demons by\nBeelzebul. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 11:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if I cast out demons by Beelzebul, by whom do your children cast them out? Therefore they will be your judges.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 11:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if I by Allah’s finger cast out demons, then Allah’s Kingdom has come to\nyou."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 11:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When the strong man, fully armed, guards his own dwelling, his goods are safe.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 11:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when someone stronger attacks him and overcomes him, he takes from him his whole armour in which he trusted, and\ndivides his plunder. "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 11:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He that is not with me is against me. He who doesn’t gather with me scatters.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 11:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The unclean spirit, when he has gone out of the man, passes through dry places, seeking rest, and finding none, he\nsays, ‘I will turn back to my house from which I came out.’ "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 11:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When he returns, he finds it swept and put in order. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 11:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then he goes, and takes seven other spirits more evil than himself, and they enter in and dwell there. The last\nstate of that man becomes worse than the first.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 11:27"},"It came to pass, as he said these things, a certain woman out of the multitude lifted up her voice, and said to him,\n“Blessed is the womb that bore you, and the breasts which nursed you!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 11:28"},"But he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“On the contrary, blessed are those who hear the word of Allah, and keep\nit.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 11:29"},"When the multitudes were gathering together to him, he began to say,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This is an evil generation. It seeks after a sign. No sign will be given to it but the sign of Yunus, the prophet.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 11:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For even as Yunus became a sign to the Ninevites, so the Son of Man will also be to this generation.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 11:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The Queen of the South will rise up in the judgement with the men of this generation, and will condemn them: for she\ncame from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Sulaiman; and behold, one greater than Sulaiman is here.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 11:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The men of Nineveh will stand up in the judgement with this generation, and will condemn it: for they repented at\nthe preaching of Yunus, and behold, one greater than Yunus is here."]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 11:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“No one, when he has lit a lamp, puts it in a cellar or under a basket, but on a stand, that those who come in may\nsee the light. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 11:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The lamp of the body is the eye. Therefore when your eye is good, your whole body is also full of light; but when it\nis evil, your body also is full of darkness. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 11:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore see whether the light that is in you isn’t darkness.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 11:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If therefore your whole body is full of light, having no part dark, it will be wholly full of light, as when the\nlamp with its bright shining gives you light.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 11:37"},"Now as he spoke, a certain Pharisee asked him to dine with him. He went in, and sat at the table.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 11:38"},"When the Pharisee saw it, he marvelled that he had not first washed himself before dinner.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 11:39"},"The Lord said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now you Pharisees cleanse the outside of the cup and of the platter, but your inward part is\nfull of extortion and wickedness. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 11:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You foolish ones, didn’t he who made the outside make the inside also?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 11:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But give for gifts to the needy those things which are within, and behold, all things will be clean to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 11:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But woe to you Pharisees! For you tithe mint and rue and every herb, but you bypass justice and Allah’s love. You\nought to have done these, and not to have left the other undone.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 11:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you Pharisees! For you love the best seats in the synagogues, and the greetings in the marketplaces.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 11:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you are like hidden graves, and the men who walk over them don’t\nknow it.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 11:45"},"One of the lawyers answered him, “Teacher, in saying this you insult us also.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 11:46"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woe to you lawyers also! For you load men with burdens that are difficult to carry, and you yourselves\nwon’t even lift one finger to help carry those burdens. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 11:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you! For you build the tombs of the prophets, and your fathers killed them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 11:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["So you testify and consent to the works of your fathers. For they killed them, and you build their tombs.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 11:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore also the wisdom of Allah said, ‘I will send to them prophets and apostles; and some of them they will kill\nand persecute, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 11:50"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that the blood of all the prophets, which was shed from the foundation of the world, may be required of this\ngeneration; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 11:51"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["from the blood of Habil to the blood of Zachariah, who perished between the altar and the sanctuary.’ Yes, I tell\nyou, it will be required of this generation. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 11:52"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to you lawyers! For you took away the key of knowledge. You didn’t enter in yourselves, and those who were\nentering in, you hindered.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 11:53"},"As he said these things to them, the scribes and the Pharisees began to be terribly angry, and to draw many things out of\nhim; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 11:54"},"lying in wait for him, and seeking to catch him in something he might say, that they might accuse him.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"LUK 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 12:1"},"Meanwhile, when a multitude of many thousands had gathered together, so much so that they trampled on each other, he began\nto tell his disciples first of all, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 12:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But there is nothing covered up that will not be revealed, nor hidden that will not be known.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 12:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore whatever you have said in the darkness will be heard in the light. What you have spoken in the ear in the\ninner rooms will be proclaimed on the housetops."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 12:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, my friends, don’t be afraid of those who kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 12:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I will warn you whom you should fear. Fear him who after he has killed, has power to cast into\nGehenna."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Yes, I tell you, fear\nhim."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 12:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Aren’t five sparrows sold for two assaria coins"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["An assarion was a small copper coin worth about an hour’s wages for an agricultural\nlabourer."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["? Not one of them is forgotten by Allah. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 12:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the very hairs of your head are all counted. Therefore don’t be afraid. You are of more value than many\nsparrows."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 12:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, everyone who confesses me before men, the Son of Man will also confess before the angels of Allah;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 12:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but he who denies me in the presence of men will be denied in the presence of Allah’s angels.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 12:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Everyone who speaks a word against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but those who blaspheme against the Holy Spirit\nwill not be forgiven. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 12:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When they bring you before the synagogues, the rulers, and the authorities, don’t be anxious how or what you will\nanswer, or what you will say; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 12:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for the Holy Spirit will teach you in that same hour what you must\nsay.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 12:13"},"One of the multitude said to him, “Teacher, tell my brother to divide the inheritance with me.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 12:14"},"But he said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Man, who made me a judge or an arbitrator over\nyou?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 12:15"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Beware! Keep yourselves from covetousness, for a man’s life doesn’t consist of the abundance of the\nthings which he possesses.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 12:16"},"He spoke a parable to them, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The ground of a certain rich man produced abundantly.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 12:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He reasoned within himself, saying, ‘What will I do, because I don’t have room to store my crops?’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 12:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said, ‘This is what I will do. I will pull down my barns, build bigger ones, and there I will store all my grain\nand my goods. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 12:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will tell my soul, “Soul, you have many goods laid up for many years. Take your ease, eat, drink, and be\nmerry.”’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 12:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But Allah said to him, ‘You foolish one, tonight your soul is required of you. The things which you have\nprepared—whose will they be?’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 12:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["So is he who lays up treasure for himself, and is not rich towards\nAllah.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 12:22"},"He said to his disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Therefore I tell you, don’t be anxious for your life, what you will eat, nor yet for your\nbody, what you will wear. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 12:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Life is more than food, and the body is more than clothing.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 12:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Consider the ravens: they don’t sow, they don’t reap, they have no warehouse or barn, and Allah feeds them. How much\nmore valuable are you than birds! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 12:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Which of you by being anxious can add a cubit"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:25 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["to his height? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 12:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If then you aren’t able to do even the least things, why are you anxious about the rest?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 12:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Consider the lilies, how they grow. They don’t toil, neither do they spin; yet I tell you, even Sulaiman in all his\nglory was not arrayed like one of these. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 12:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if this is how Allah clothes the grass in the field, which today exists, and tomorrow is cast into the oven, how\nmuch more will he clothe you, O you of little faith? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 12:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t seek what you will eat or what you will drink; neither be anxious.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 12:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the nations of the world seek after all of these things, but your Father knows that you need these things.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 12:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But seek Allah’s Kingdom, and all these things will be added to you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 12:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Don’t be afraid, little flock, for it is your Father’s good pleasure to give you the Kingdom.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 12:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Sell that which you have, and give gifts to the needy. Make for yourselves purses which don’t grow old, a treasure\nin the heavens that doesn’t fail, where no thief approaches, neither moth destroys.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 12:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 12:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Let your waist be dressed and your lamps burning. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 12:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Be like men watching for their lord, when he returns from the wedding feast; that when he comes and knocks, they may\nimmediately open to him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 12:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed are those servants, whom the lord will find watching when he comes. Most certainly I tell you that he will\ndress himself, make them recline, and will come and serve them. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 12:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will be blessed if he comes in the second or third watch, and finds them so.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 12:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But know this, that if the master of the house had known in what hour the thief was coming, he would have watched,\nand not allowed his house to be broken into. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 12:40"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore be ready also, for the Son of Man is coming in an hour that you don’t expect\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 12:41"},"Peter said to him, “Lord, are you telling this parable to us, or to everybody?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 12:42"},"The Lord said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Who then is the faithful and wise steward, whom his lord will set over his household, to give them\ntheir portion of food at the right times? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 12:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Blessed is that servant whom his lord will find doing so when he comes.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 12:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Truly I tell you, that he will set him over all that he has.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 12:45"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But if that servant says in his heart, ‘My lord delays his coming,’ and begins to beat the menservants and the\nmaidservants, and to eat and drink, and to be drunken, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 12:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["then the lord of that servant will come in a day when he isn’t expecting him, and in an hour that he doesn’t know,\nand will cut him in two, and place his portion with the unfaithful.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 12:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["That servant, who knew his lord’s will, and didn’t prepare, nor do what he wanted, will be beaten with many stripes,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 12:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but he who didn’t know, and did things worthy of stripes, will be beaten with few stripes. To whomever much is\ngiven, of him will much be required; and to whom much was entrusted, of him more will be asked.\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 12:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I came to throw fire on the earth. I wish it were already kindled.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 12:50"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But I have a baptism to be baptised with, and how distressed I am until it is accomplished!\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 12:51"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Do you think that I have come to give peace in the earth? I tell you, no, but rather division.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 12:52"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For from now on, there will be five in one house divided, three against two, and two against three.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 12:53"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will be divided, father against son, and son against father; mother against daughter, and daughter against her\nmother; mother-in-law against her daughter-in-law, and daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.”\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:53 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Micah 7:6"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 12:54"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said to the multitudes also, “When you see a cloud rising from the west, immediately you say, ‘A shower is\ncoming,’ and so it happens. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 12:55"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When a south wind blows, you say, ‘There will be a scorching heat,’ and it happens.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 12:56"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You hypocrites! You know how to interpret the appearance of the earth and the sky, but how is it that you don’t\ninterpret this time? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"LUK 12:57"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Why don’t you judge for yourselves what is right? "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"LUK 12:58"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For when you are going with your adversary before the magistrate, try diligently on the way to be released from him,\nlest perhaps he drag you to the judge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and the officer throw you into prison.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"LUK 12:59"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, you will by no means get out of there, until you have paid the very last\npenny."]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:59 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, lepton. A lepton is a very small brass Jewish coin worth half a Roman quadrans each,\nwhich is worth a quarter of the copper assarion. Lepta are worth less than 1% of an agricultural worker’s daily\nwages."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"LUK 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 13:1"},"Now there were some present at the same time who told him about the Galileans, whose blood Pilate had mixed with their\nsacrifices. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 13:2"},"Isa answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you think that these Galileans were worse sinners than all the other Galileans, because they\nsuffered such things? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 13:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, no, but unless you repent, you will all perish in the same way.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 13:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or those eighteen, on whom the tower in Siloam fell and killed them; do you think that they were worse offenders than\nall the men who dwell in Jerusalem? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 13:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, no, but, unless you repent, you will all perish in the same\nway.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 13:6"},"He spoke this parable. ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain man had a fig tree planted in his vineyard, and he came seeking fruit on it, and\nfound none. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 13:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said to the vine dresser, ‘Behold, these three years I have come looking for fruit on this fig tree, and found\nnone. Cut it down. Why does it waste the soil?’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 13:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He answered, ‘Lord, leave it alone this year also, until I dig around it and fertilise it.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 13:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If it bears fruit, fine; but if not, after that, you can cut it\ndown.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 13:10"},"He was teaching in one of the synagogues on the Sabbath day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 13:11"},"Behold, there was a woman who had a spirit of infirmity eighteen years. She was bent over, and could in no way straighten\nherself up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 13:12"},"When Isa saw her, he called her, and said to her, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Woman, you are freed from your\ninfirmity.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 13:13"},"He laid his hands on her, and immediately she stood up straight and glorified Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 13:14"},"The ruler of the synagogue, being indignant because Isa had healed on the Sabbath, said to the multitude, “There are six\ndays in which men ought to work. Therefore come on those days and be healed, and not on the Sabbath day!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 13:15"},"Therefore the Lord answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You hypocrites! Doesn’t each one of you free his ox or his donkey from the stall on\nthe Sabbath, and lead him away to water? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 13:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Ought not this woman, being a daughter of Ibrahim whom Iblis had bound eighteen long years, be freed from this\nbondage on the Sabbath day?” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 13:17"},"As he said these things, all his adversaries were disappointed and all the multitude rejoiced for all the glorious things\nthat were done by him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 13:18"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What is Allah’s Kingdom like? To what shall I compare it?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 13:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is like a grain of mustard seed which a man took and put in his own garden. It grew and became a large tree, and\nthe birds of the sky live in its branches.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 13:20"},"Again he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“To what shall I compare Allah’s Kingdom?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 13:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is like yeast, which a woman took and hid in three measures\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, three sata. 3 sata is about 39 litres or a bit more than a\nbushel."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of flour, until it was all leavened.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 13:22"},"He went on his way through cities and villages, teaching, and travelling on to Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 13:23"},"One said to him, “Lord, are they few who are saved?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to them, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 13:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Strive to enter in by the narrow door, for many, I tell you, will seek to enter in and will not be able.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 13:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When once the master of the house has risen up, and has shut the door, and you begin to stand outside and to knock\nat the door, saying, ‘Lord, Lord, open to us!’ then he will answer and tell you, ‘I don’t know you or where you come from.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 13:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then you will begin to say, ‘We ate and drank in your presence, and you taught in our streets.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 13:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He will say, ‘I tell you, I don’t know where you come from. Depart from me, all you workers of iniquity.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 13:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth when you see Ibrahim, Isḥāq, Yaqub, and all the prophets in Allah’s\nKingdom, and yourselves being thrown outside. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 13:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will come from the east, west, north, and south, and will sit down in Allah’s Kingdom.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 13:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, there are some who are last who will be first, and there are some who are first who will be\nlast.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 13:31"},"On that same day, some Pharisees came, saying to him, “Get out of here, and go away, for Herod wants to kill you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 13:32"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go and tell that fox, ‘Behold, I cast out demons and perform cures today and tomorrow, and the\nthird day I complete my mission. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 13:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Nevertheless I must go on my way today and tomorrow and the next day, for it can’t be that a prophet would perish\noutside of Jerusalem.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 13:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you who kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to her! How often I wanted to gather\nyour children together, like a hen gathers her own brood under her wings, and you refused!\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 13:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, your house is left to you desolate. I tell you, you will not see me until you say, ‘Blessed is he who comes\nin the name of the Lord!’” "]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 118:26"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"LUK 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 14:1"},"When he went into the house of one of the rulers of the Pharisees on a Sabbath to eat bread, they were watching him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 14:2"},"Behold, a certain man who had dropsy was in front of him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 14:3"},"Isa, answering, spoke to the lawyers and Pharisees, saying,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 14:4"},"But they were silent. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He took him, and healed him, and let him go. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 14:5"},"He answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Which of you, if your son"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:5\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “donkey” instead of “son”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["or an ox fell into a well, wouldn’t immediately pull him out on a Sabbath\nday?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 14:6"},"They couldn’t answer him regarding these things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 14:7"},"He spoke a parable to those who were invited, when he noticed how they chose the best seats, and said to them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 14:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When you are invited by anyone to a wedding feast, don’t sit in the best seat, since perhaps someone more honourable\nthan you might be invited by him, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 14:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and he who invited both of you would come and tell you, ‘Make room for this person.’ Then you would begin, with\nshame, to take the lowest place. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 14:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when you are invited, go and sit in the lowest place, so that when he who invited you comes, he may tell you,\n‘Friend, move up higher.’ Then you will be honoured in the presence of all who sit at the table with you.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 14:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be\nexalted.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 14:12"},"He also said to the one who had invited him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When you make a dinner or a supper, don’t call your friends, nor your\nbrothers, nor your kinsmen, nor rich neighbours, or perhaps they might also return the favour, and pay you back.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 14:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when you make a feast, ask the poor, the maimed, the lame, or the blind;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 14:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and you will be blessed, because they don’t have the resources to repay you. For you will be repaid in the\nresurrection of the righteous.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 14:15"},"When one of those who sat at the table with him heard these things, he said to him, “Blessed is he who will feast in\nAllah’s Kingdom!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 14:16"},"But he said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain man made a great supper, and he invited many people.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 14:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He sent out his servant at supper time to tell those who were invited, ‘Come, for everything is ready now.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 14:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They all as one began to make excuses."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The first said to him, ‘I have bought a field, and I must go and see it. Please have me\nexcused.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 14:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Another said, ‘I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I must go try them out. Please have me\nexcused.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 14:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Another said, ‘I have married a wife, and therefore I can’t come.’\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 14:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“That servant came, and told his lord these things. Then the master of the house, being angry, said to his servant,\n‘Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and bring in the poor, maimed, blind, and\nlame.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 14:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The servant said, ‘Lord, it is done as you commanded, and there is still\nroom.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 14:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The lord said to the servant, ‘Go out into the highways and hedges, and compel them to come in, that my house may\nbe filled. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 14:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For I tell you that none of those men who were invited will taste of my\nsupper.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 14:25"},"Now great multitudes were going with him. He turned and said to them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 14:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If anyone comes to me, and doesn’t disregard"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, hate "]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["his own father, mother, wife, children, brothers, and sisters, yes, and his own life also, he\ncan’t be my disciple. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 14:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whoever doesn’t bear his own cross, and come after me, can’t be my disciple.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 14:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For which of you, desiring to build a tower, doesn’t first sit down and count the cost, to see if he has enough to\ncomplete it? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 14:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or perhaps, when he has laid a foundation, and is not able to finish, everyone who sees begins to mock him,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 14:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["saying, ‘This man began to build, and wasn’t able to finish.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 14:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or what king, as he goes to encounter another king in war, will not sit down first and consider whether he is able\nwith ten thousand to meet him who comes against him with twenty thousand?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 14:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or else, while the other is yet a great way off, he sends an envoy, and asks for conditions of peace.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 14:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["So therefore whoever of you who doesn’t renounce all that he has, he can’t be my disciple.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 14:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Salt is good, but if the salt becomes flat and tasteless, with what do you season it?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 14:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It is fit neither for the soil nor for the manure pile. It is thrown out. He who has ears to hear, let him\nhear.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"LUK 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 15:1"},"Now all the tax collectors and sinners were coming close to him to hear him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 15:2"},"The Pharisees and the scribes murmured, saying, “This man welcomes sinners, and eats with them.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 15:3"},"He told them this parable. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 15:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Which of you men, if you had one hundred sheep, and lost one of them, wouldn’t leave the ninety-nine in the\nwilderness, and go after the one that was lost, until he found it?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 15:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When he has found it, he carries it on his shoulders, rejoicing.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 15:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When he comes home, he calls together his friends and his neighbours, saying to them, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have\nfound my sheep which was lost!’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 15:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you that even so there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents, than over ninety-nine righteous\npeople who need no repentance. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 15:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Or what woman, if she had ten drachma"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:8\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A drachma coin was worth about 2 days wages for an agricultural\nlabourer."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["coins, if she lost one drachma coin, wouldn’t light a lamp, sweep the house, and seek diligently until she\nfound it? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 15:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When she has found it, she calls together her friends and neighbours, saying, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have found the\ndrachma which I had lost.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 15:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Even so, I tell you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of Allah over one sinner\nrepenting.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 15:11"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain man had two sons. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 15:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The younger of them said to his father, ‘Father, give me my share of your property.’ He divided his livelihood\nbetween them. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 15:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Not many days after, the younger son gathered all of this together and travelled into a far country. There he wasted\nhis property with riotous living. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 15:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When he had spent all of it, there arose a severe famine in that country, and he began to be in need.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 15:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He went and joined himself to one of the citizens of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed pigs.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 15:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He wanted to fill his belly with the husks that the pigs ate, but no one gave him any.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 15:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when he came to himself he said, ‘How many hired servants of my father’s have bread enough to spare, and I’m\ndying with hunger! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 15:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I will get up and go to my father, and will tell him, “Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in your sight.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 15:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I am no more worthy to be called your son. Make me as one of your hired\nservants.”’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 15:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He arose, and came to his father. But while he was still far off, his father saw him, and was moved with\ncompassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 15:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The son said to him, ‘Father, I have sinned against heaven and in your sight. I am no longer worthy to be called\nyour son.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 15:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But the father said to his servants, ‘Bring out the best robe, and put it on him. Put a ring on his hand, and\nsandals on his feet. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 15:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Bring the fattened calf, kill it, and let’s eat, and celebrate;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 15:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for this, my son, was dead, and is alive again. He was lost, and is found.’ Then they began to\ncelebrate."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 15:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now his elder son was in the field. As he came near to the house, he heard music and dancing.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 15:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He called one of the servants to him, and asked what was going on.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 15:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said to him, ‘Your brother has come, and your father has killed the fattened calf, because he has received him\nback safe and healthy.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 15:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But he was angry, and would not go in. Therefore his father came out, and begged him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 15:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But he answered his father, ‘Behold, these many years I have served you, and I never disobeyed a commandment of\nyours, but you never gave me a goat, that I might celebrate with my friends.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 15:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when this your son came, who has devoured your living with prostitutes, you killed the fattened calf for\nhim.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 15:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said to him, ‘Son, you are always with me, and all that is mine is yours.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 15:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But it was appropriate to celebrate and be glad, for this, your brother, was dead, and is alive again. He was lost,\nand is found.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"LUK 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 16:1"},"He also said to his disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“There was a certain rich man who had a manager. An accusation was made to him that\nthis man was wasting his possessions. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 16:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He called him, and said to him, ‘What is this that I hear about you? Give an accounting of your management, for you\ncan no longer be manager.’ "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 16:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The manager said within himself, ‘What will I do, seeing that my lord is taking away the management position from\nme? I don’t have strength to dig. I am ashamed to beg. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 16:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I know what I will do, so that when I am removed from management, they may receive me into their houses.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 16:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Calling each one of his lord’s debtors to him, he said to the first, ‘How much do you owe to my lord?’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 16:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said, ‘A hundred batos"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["100 batos is about 395 litres or 104 U. S.\ngallons."]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of oil.’ He said to him, ‘Take your bill, and sit down quickly and write fifty.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 16:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then he said to another, ‘How much do you owe?’ He said, ‘A hundred\ncors"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["100 cors = about 2,110 litres or 600 bushels."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["of wheat.’ He said to him, ‘Take your bill, and write eighty.’"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 16:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“His lord commended the dishonest manager because he had done wisely, for the children of this world are, in their\nown generation, wiser than the children of the light. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 16:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, make for yourselves friends by means of unrighteous mammon, so that when you fail, they may receive you\ninto the eternal tents. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 16:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He who is faithful in a very little is faithful also in much. He who is dishonest in a very little is also dishonest\nin much. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 16:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If therefore you have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true riches?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 16:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If you have not been faithful in that which is another’s, who will give you that which is your own?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 16:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["No servant can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to one,\nand despise the other. You aren’t able to serve Allah and Mammon.”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Mammon” refers to riches or a false god of wealth."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 16:14"},"The Pharisees, who were lovers of money, also heard all these things, and they scoffed at him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 16:15"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You are those who justify yourselves in the sight of men, but Allah knows your hearts. For that\nwhich is exalted amongst men is an abomination in the sight of Allah.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 16:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The law and the prophets were until Yahya. From that time the Good News of Allah’s Kingdom is preached, and everyone\nis forcing his way into it. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 16:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away, than for one tiny stroke of a pen in the law to fall.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 16:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Everyone who divorces his wife and marries another commits adultery. He who marries one who is divorced from a\nhusband commits adultery. "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 16:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Now there was a certain rich man, and he was clothed in purple and fine linen, living in luxury every day.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 16:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A certain beggar, named Lazarus, was taken to his gate, full of sores,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 16:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and desiring to be fed with the crumbs that fell from the rich man’s table. Yes, even the dogs came and licked his\nsores. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 16:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The beggar died, and he was carried away by the angels to Ibrahim’s bosom. The rich man also died, and was buried.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 16:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In Hades,"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["he lifted up his eyes, being in torment, and saw Ibrahim far off,\nand Lazarus at his bosom. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 16:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He cried and said, ‘Father Ibrahim, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus, that he may dip the tip of his finger in\nwater, and cool my tongue! For I am in anguish in this flame.’"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 16:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But Ibrahim said, ‘Son, remember that you, in your lifetime, received your good things, and Lazarus, in the same\nway, bad things. But here he is now comforted, and you are in anguish.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 16:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Besides all this, between us and you there is a great gulf fixed, that those who want to pass from here to you are\nnot able, and that no one may cross over from there to us.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 16:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said, ‘I ask you therefore, father, that you would send him to my father’s house;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 16:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I have five brothers, that he may testify to them, so they won’t also come into this place of\ntorment.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 16:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But Ibrahim said to him, ‘They have Musa and the prophets. Let them listen to\nthem.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 16:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said, ‘No, father Ibrahim, but if one goes to them from the dead, they will\nrepent.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 16:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said to him, ‘If they don’t listen to Musa and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded if one rises from\nthe dead.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"LUK 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 17:1"},"He said to the disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is impossible that no occasions of stumbling should come, but woe to him through whom\nthey come! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 17:2"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It would be better for him if a millstone were hung around his neck, and he were thrown into the sea, rather than\nthat he should cause one of these little ones to stumble. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 17:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Be careful. If your brother sins against you, rebuke him. If he repents, forgive him.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 17:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If he sins against you seven times in the day, and seven times returns, saying, ‘I repent,’ you shall forgive\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 17:5"},"The apostles said to the Lord, “Increase our faith.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 17:6"},"The Lord said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you had faith like a grain of mustard seed, you would tell this sycamore tree, ‘Be uprooted, and be\nplanted in the sea,’ and it would obey you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 17:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But who is there amongst you, having a servant ploughing or keeping sheep, that will say when he comes in from the\nfield, ‘Come immediately and sit down at the table,’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 17:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and will not rather tell him, ‘Prepare my supper, clothe yourself properly, and serve me, while I eat and drink.\nAfterward you shall eat and drink’? "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 17:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Does he thank that servant because he did the things that were commanded? I think not.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 17:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Even so you also, when you have done all the things that are commanded you, say, ‘We are unworthy servants. We have\ndone our duty.’” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 17:11"},"As he was on his way to Jerusalem, he was passing along the borders of Samaria and Galilee.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 17:12"},"As he entered into a certain village, ten men who were lepers met him, who stood at a distance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 17:13"},"They lifted up their voices, saying, “Isa, Master, have mercy on us!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 17:14"},"When he saw them, he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go and show yourselves to the\npriests.”"]}," As they went, they were cleansed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 17:15"},"One of them, when he saw that he was healed, turned back, glorifying Allah with a loud voice.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 17:16"},"He fell on his face at Isa’s feet, giving him thanks; and he was a Samaritan.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 17:17"},"Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Weren’t the ten cleansed? But where are the nine?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 17:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Were there none found who returned to give glory to Allah, except this\nforeigner?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 17:19"},"Then he said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Get up, and go your way. Your faith has healed\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 17:20"},"Being asked by the Pharisees when Allah’s Kingdom would come, he answered them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Allah’s Kingdom doesn’t come with observation; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 17:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["neither will they say, ‘Look, here!’ or, ‘Look, there!’ for behold, Allah’s Kingdom is within\nyou.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 17:22"},"He said to the disciples, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The days will come when you will desire to see one of the days of the Son of Man, and you\nwill not see it. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 17:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will tell you, ‘Look, here!’ or ‘Look, there!’ Don’t go away or follow after them,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 17:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for as the lightning, when it flashes out of one part under the sky, shines to another part under the sky; so will\nthe Son of Man be in his day. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 17:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But first, he must suffer many things and be rejected by this generation.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 17:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["As it was in the days of Nuh, even so will it be also in the days of the Son of Man.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 17:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They ate, they drank, they married, and they were given in marriage until the day that Nuh entered into the ship,\nand the flood came and destroyed them all. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 17:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Likewise, even as it was in the days of Lut: they ate, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they built;\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 17:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but in the day that Lut went out from Sodom, it rained fire and sulphur from the sky and destroyed them all.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 17:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It will be the same way in the day that the Son of Man is revealed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 17:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["In that day, he who will be on the housetop and his goods in the house, let him not go down to take them away. Let\nhim who is in the field likewise not turn back. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 17:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Remember Lut’s wife! "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 17:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Whoever seeks to save his life loses it, but whoever loses his life preserves it.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 17:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, in that night there will be two people in one bed. One will be taken and the other will be left.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 17:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["There will be two grinding grain together. One will be taken and the other will be\nleft.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 17:36"},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:36 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some Greek manuscripts add: “Two will be in the field: the one taken, and the other\nleft.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 17:37"},"They, answering, asked him, “Where, Lord?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Where the body is, there the vultures will also be gathered\ntogether.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"LUK 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 18:1"},"He also spoke a parable to them that they must always pray, and not give up,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 18:2"},"saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“There was a judge in a certain city who didn’t fear Allah, and didn’t respect man.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 18:3"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["A widow was in that city, and she often came to him, saying, ‘Defend me from my adversary!’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 18:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He wouldn’t for a while, but afterward he said to himself, ‘Though I neither fear Allah, nor respect man,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 18:5"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["yet because this widow bothers me, I will defend her, or else she will wear me out by her continual\ncoming.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 18:6"},"The Lord said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Listen to what the unrighteous judge says.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 18:7"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Won’t Allah avenge his chosen ones who are crying out to him day and night, and yet he exercises patience with them?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 18:8"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you that he will avenge them quickly. Nevertheless, when the Son of Man comes, will he find faith on the\nearth?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 18:9"},"He spoke also this parable to certain people who were convinced of their own righteousness, and who despised all others.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 18:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Two men went up into the temple to pray; one was a Pharisee, and the other was a tax collector.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 18:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The Pharisee stood and prayed to himself like this: ‘Allah, I thank you that I am not like the rest of men,\nextortionists, unrighteous, adulterers, or even like this tax collector.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 18:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I fast twice a week. I give tithes of all that I get.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 18:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But the tax collector, standing far away, wouldn’t even lift up his eyes to heaven, but beat his breast, saying,\n‘Allah, be merciful to me, a sinner!’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 18:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other; for everyone who exalts himself will be\nhumbled, but he who humbles himself will be exalted.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 18:15"},"They were also bringing their babies to him, that he might touch them. But when the disciples saw it, they rebuked them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 18:16"},"Isa summoned them, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Allow the little children to come to me, and don’t hinder them, for Allah’s Kingdom\nbelongs to such as these. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 18:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly, I tell you, whoever doesn’t receive Allah’s Kingdom like a little child, he will in no way enter\ninto it.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 18:18"},"A certain ruler asked him, saying, “Good Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 18:19"},"Isa asked him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why do you call me good? No one is good, except one: Allah.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 18:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You know the commandments: ‘Don’t commit adultery,’ ‘Don’t murder,’ ‘Don’t steal,’ ‘Don’t give false testimony,’\n‘Honour your father and your mother.’”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["18:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus\n20:12-16; Deuteronomy 5:16-20"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 18:21"},"He said, “I have observed all these things from my youth up.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 18:22"},"When Isa heard these things, he said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You still lack one thing. Sell all that you have, and distribute it to\nthe poor. Then you will have treasure in heaven; then come, follow\nme.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 18:23"},"But when he heard these things, he became very sad, for he was very rich.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 18:24"},"Isa, seeing that he became very sad, said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“How hard it is for those who have riches to enter into Allah’s Kingdom!\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 18:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For it is easier for a camel to enter in through a needle’s eye than for a rich man to enter into Allah’s\nKingdom.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 18:26"},"Those who heard it said, “Then who can be saved?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 18:27"},"But he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The things which are impossible with men are possible with\nAllah.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 18:28"},"Peter said, “Look, we have left everything and followed you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 18:29"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Most certainly I tell you, there is no one who has left house, or wife, or brothers, or parents, or\nchildren, for Allah’s Kingdom’s sake, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 18:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["who will not receive many times more in this time, and in the world to come, eternal\nlife.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 18:31"},"He took the twelve aside, and said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and all the things that are\nwritten through the prophets concerning the Son of Man will be completed.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 18:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For he will be delivered up to the Gentiles, will be mocked, treated shamefully, and spit on.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 18:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will scourge and kill him. On the third day, he will rise\nagain.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 18:34"},"They understood none of these things. This saying was hidden from them, and they didn’t understand the things that were\nsaid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 18:35"},"As he came near Jericho, a certain blind man sat by the road, begging.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 18:36"},"Hearing a multitude going by, he asked what this meant. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 18:37"},"They told him that Isa of Nazareth was passing by. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 18:38"},"He cried out, “Isa, you son of Dawood, have mercy on me!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 18:39"},"Those who led the way rebuked him, that he should be quiet; but he cried out all the more, “You son of Dawood, have mercy\non me!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 18:40"},"Standing still, Isa commanded him to be brought to him. When he had come near, he asked him,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 18:41"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What do you want me to do?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said, “Lord, that I may see again.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 18:42"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Receive your sight. Your faith has healed you.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 18:43"},"Immediately he received his sight and followed him, glorifying Allah. All the people, when they saw it, praised Allah.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"LUK 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 19:1"},"He entered and was passing through Jericho. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 19:2"},"There was a man named Zacchaeus. He was a chief tax collector, and he was rich.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 19:3"},"He was trying to see who Isa was, and couldn’t because of the crowd, because he was short.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 19:4"},"He ran on ahead, and climbed up into a sycamore tree to see him, for he was going to pass that way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 19:5"},"When Isa came to the place, he looked up and saw him, and said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Zacchaeus, hurry and come down, for today I must stay at your house.”\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 19:6"},"He hurried, came down, and received him joyfully. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 19:7"},"When they saw it, they all murmured, saying, “He has gone in to lodge with a man who is a sinner.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 19:8"},"Zacchaeus stood and said to the Lord, “Behold, Lord, half of my goods I give to the poor. If I have wrongfully exacted\nanything of anyone, I restore four times as much.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 19:9"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Today, salvation has come to this house, because he also is a son of Ibrahim.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 19:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the Son of Man came to seek and to save that which was lost.”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 19:11"},"As they heard these things, he went on and told a parable, because he was near Jerusalem, and they supposed that Allah’s\nKingdom would be revealed immediately. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 19:12"},"He said therefore, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself a kingdom and to return.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 19:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He called ten servants of his and gave them ten mina coins,\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["10 minas was more than 3 years’ wages for an agricultural labourer.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and told them, ‘Conduct business until I come.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 19:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But his citizens hated him, and sent an envoy after him, saying, ‘We don’t want this man to reign over\nus.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 19:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When he had come back again, having received the kingdom, he commanded these servants, to whom he had given the\nmoney, to be called to him, that he might know what they had gained by conducting business.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 19:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The first came before him, saying, ‘Lord, your mina has made ten more\nminas.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 19:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said to him, ‘Well done, you good servant! Because you were found faithful with very little, you shall have\nauthority over ten cities.’ "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 19:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The second came, saying, ‘Your mina, Lord, has made five minas.’\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 19:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“So he said to him, ‘And you are to be over five cities.’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 19:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Another came, saying, ‘Lord, behold, your mina, which I kept laid away in a handkerchief,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 19:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I feared you, because you are an exacting man. You take up that which you didn’t lay down, and reap that which\nyou didn’t sow.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 19:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“He said to him, ‘Out of your own mouth I will judge you, you wicked servant! You knew that I am an exacting man,\ntaking up that which I didn’t lay down, and reaping that which I didn’t sow.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 19:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then why didn’t you deposit my money in the bank, and at my coming, I might have earned interest on it?’\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 19:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He said to those who stood by, ‘Take the mina away from him and give it to him who has the ten\nminas.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 19:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“They said to him, ‘Lord, he has ten minas!’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 19:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘For I tell you that to everyone who has, will more be given; but from him who doesn’t have, even that which he has\nwill be taken away from him. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 19:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But bring those enemies of mine who didn’t want me to reign over them here, and kill them before\nme.’”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 19:28"},"Having said these things, he went on ahead, going up to Jerusalem.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 19:29"},"When he came near to Bethsphage",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR, NU read “Bethpage” instead of\n“Bethsphage”"]}],"caller":"+"}," and Bethany, at the mountain that is called Olivet, he sent two of his disciples,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 19:30"},"saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go your way into the village on the other side, in which, as you enter, you will find a colt tied, which no\nman had ever sat upon. Untie it and bring it. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 19:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["If anyone asks you, ‘Why are you untying it?’ say to him: ‘The Lord needs\nit.’”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 19:32"},"Those who were sent went away, and found things just as he had told them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 19:33"},"As they were untying the colt, its owners said to them, “Why are you untying the colt?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 19:34"},"They said, “The Lord needs it.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 19:35"},"Then they brought it to Isa. They threw their cloaks on the colt, and sat Isa on them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 19:36"},"As he went, they spread their cloaks on the road. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 19:37"},"As he was now getting near, at the descent of the Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice\nand praise Allah with a loud voice for all the mighty works which they had seen,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 19:38"},"saying, “Blessed is the King who comes in the name of the Lord!\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 118:26"]}],"caller":"+"}," Peace in heaven, and glory in the highest!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 19:39"},"Some of the Pharisees from the multitude said to him, “Teacher, rebuke your disciples!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 19:40"},"He answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you that if these were silent, the stones would cry\nout.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 19:41"},"When he came near, he saw the city and wept over it, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 19:42"},"saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If you, even you, had known today the things which belong to your peace! But now, they are hidden from your\neyes. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 19:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For the days will come on you, when your enemies will throw up a barricade against you, surround you, hem you in on\nevery side, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 19:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and will dash you and your children within you to the ground. They will not leave in you one stone on another,\nbecause you didn’t know the time of your visitation.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 19:45"},"He entered into the temple, and began to drive out those who bought and sold in it,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 19:46"},"saying to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“It is written, ‘My house is a house of prayer,’\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:46 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 56:7"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but you have made it a ‘den of robbers’!”\n"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["19:46 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 7:11"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 19:47"},"He was teaching daily in the temple, but the chief priests, the scribes, and the leading men amongst the people sought to\ndestroy him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 19:48"},"They couldn’t find what they might do, for all the people hung on to every word that he said.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"LUK 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 20:1"},"On one of those days, as he was teaching the people in the temple and preaching the Good News, the\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “chief”"]}],"caller":"+"},"priests and scribes came to him with the elders.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 20:2"},"They asked him, “Tell us: by what authority do you do these things? Or who is giving you this authority?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 20:3"},"He answered them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I also will ask you one question. Tell me:\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 20:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["the baptism of Yahya, was it from heaven, or from men?”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 20:5"},"They reasoned with themselves, saying, “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ he will say, ‘Why didn’t you believe him?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 20:6"},"But if we say, ‘From men,’ all the people will stone us, for they are persuaded that Yahya was a prophet.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 20:7"},"They answered that they didn’t know where it was from. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 20:8"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these\nthings.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 20:9"},"He began to tell the people this parable. ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“A "]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:9\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU (in brackets) and TR add “certain”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["man planted a vineyard, and rented it out to some farmers, and went into\nanother country for a long time. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 20:10"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["At the proper season, he sent a servant to the farmers to collect his share of the fruit of the vineyard. But the\nfarmers beat him, and sent him away empty. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 20:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He sent yet another servant, and they also beat him, and treated him shamefully, and sent him away empty.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 20:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He sent yet a third, and they also wounded him, and threw him out.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 20:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The lord of the vineyard said, ‘What shall I do? I will send my beloved son. It may be that seeing him, they will\nrespect him.’"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 20:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But when the farmers saw him, they reasoned amongst themselves, saying, ‘This is the heir. Come, let’s kill him,\nthat the inheritance may be ours.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 20:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They threw him out of the vineyard and killed him. What therefore will the lord of the vineyard do to them?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 20:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He will come and destroy these farmers, and will give the vineyard to\nothers.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When they heard that, they said, “May that never be!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 20:17"},"But he looked at them and said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Then what is this that is\nwritten,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘The stone which the builders rejected"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["was made the chief cornerstone?’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["20:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur\n118:22 "]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 20:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces,\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but it will crush whomever it falls on to dust.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 20:19"},"The chief priests and the scribes sought to lay hands on him that very hour, but they feared the people—for they knew he\nhad spoken this parable against them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 20:20"},"They watched him and sent out spies, who pretended to be righteous, that they might trap him in something he said, so as\nto deliver him up to the power and authority of the governor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 20:21"},"They asked him, “Teacher, we know that you say and teach what is right, and aren’t partial to anyone, but truly teach the\nway of Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 20:22"},"Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 20:23"},"But he perceived their craftiness, and said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why do you test me?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 20:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Show me a denarius. Whose image and inscription are on it?”\n"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They answered, “Caesar’s.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 20:25"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Then give to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to Allah the things that are\nAllah’s.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 20:26"},"They weren’t able to trap him in his words before the people. They marvelled at his answer and were silent.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 20:27"},"Some of the Sadducees came to him, those who deny that there is a resurrection.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 20:28"},"They asked him, “Teacher, Musa wrote to us that if a man’s brother dies having a wife, and he is childless, his brother\nshould take the wife and raise up children for his brother. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 20:29"},"There were therefore seven brothers. The first took a wife, and died childless.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 20:30"},"The second took her as wife, and he died childless. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 20:31"},"The third took her, and likewise the seven all left no children, and died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 20:32"},"Afterward the woman also died. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 20:33"},"Therefore in the resurrection whose wife of them will she be? For the seven had her as a wife.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 20:34"},"Isa said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The children of this age marry, and are given in marriage.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 20:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But those who are considered worthy to attain to that age and the resurrection from the dead neither marry nor are\ngiven in marriage. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 20:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For they can’t die any more, for they are like the angels, and are children of Allah, being children of the\nresurrection. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 20:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But that the dead are raised, even Musa showed at the bush, when he called the Lord ‘The Allah of Ibrahim, Allah of\nIsḥāq, and Allah of Yaqub.’ "]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["20:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 3:6"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 20:38"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Now he is not Allah of the dead, but of the living, for all are alive to\nhim.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 20:39"},"Some of the scribes answered, “Teacher, you speak well.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 20:40"},"They didn’t dare to ask him any more questions. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 20:41"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why do they say that the Masih is Dawood’s son?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 20:42"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Dawood himself says in the book of Zabur,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["‘The Lord said to my Lord,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Sit at my right hand,"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 20:43"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["until I make your enemies the footstool of your feet.”’"]},"\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["20:43 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 110:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 20:44"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Dawood therefore calls him Lord, so how is he his son?”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 20:45"},"In the hearing of all the people, he said to his disciples,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 20:46"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Beware of those scribes who like to walk in long robes, and love greetings in the marketplaces, the best seats in\nthe synagogues, and the best places at feasts; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 20:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["who devour widows’ houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these will receive greater\ncondemnation.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"LUK 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 21:1"},"He looked up and saw the rich people who were putting their gifts into the treasury.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 21:2"},"He saw a certain poor widow casting in two small brass coins.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, “two lepta.” 2 lepta was about 1% of a day’s wages for an agricultural\nlabourer."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 21:3"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Truly I tell you, this poor widow put in more than all of them,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 21:4"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for all these put in gifts for Allah from their abundance, but she, out of her poverty, put in all that she had to\nlive on.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 21:5"},"As some were talking about the temple and how it was decorated with beautiful stones and gifts, he said,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 21:6"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“As for these things which you see, the days will come, in which there will not be left here one stone on another\nthat will not be thrown down.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 21:7"},"They asked him, “Teacher, so when will these things be? What is the sign that these things are about to happen?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 21:8"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Watch out that you don’t get led astray, for many will come in my name, saying, ‘I am\nhe"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, I AM"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":[",’ and, ‘The time is at hand.’ Therefore don’t follow them.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 21:9"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When you hear of wars and disturbances, don’t be terrified, for these things must happen first, but the end won’t\ncome immediately.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 21:10"},"Then he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 21:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["There will be great earthquakes, famines, and plagues in various places. There will be terrors and great signs from\nheaven. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 21:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But before all these things, they will lay their hands on you and will persecute you, delivering you up to\nsynagogues and prisons, bringing you before kings and governors for my name’s sake.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 21:13"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["It will turn out as a testimony for you. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 21:14"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Settle it therefore in your hearts not to meditate beforehand how to answer,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 21:15"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I will give you a mouth and wisdom which all your adversaries will not be able to withstand or to contradict.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 21:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You will be handed over even by parents, brothers, relatives, and friends. They will cause some of you to be put to\ndeath. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 21:17"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You will be hated by all men for my name’s sake. "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 21:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["And not a hair of your head will perish."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 21:19"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“By your endurance you will win your lives."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 21:20"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then know that its desolation is at hand.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 21:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains. Let those who are in the middle of her depart. Let those who\nare in the country not enter therein. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 21:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For these are days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 21:23"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Woe to those who are pregnant and to those who nurse infants in those days! For there will be great distress in the\nland, and wrath to this people. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 21:24"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["They will fall by the edge of the sword, and will be led captive into all the nations. Jerusalem will be trampled\ndown by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 21:25"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["There will be signs in the sun, moon, and stars; and on the earth anxiety of nations, in perplexity for the roaring\nof the sea and the waves; "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 21:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["men fainting for fear, and for expectation of the things which are coming on the world: for the powers of the\nheavens will be shaken. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 21:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then they will see the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 21:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But when these things begin to happen, look up and lift up your heads, because your redemption is\nnear.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 21:29"},"He told them a parable. ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“See the fig tree and all the trees.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 21:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When they are already budding, you see it and know by your own selves that the summer is already near.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 21:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Even so you also, when you see these things happening, know that Allah’s Kingdom is near.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 21:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Most certainly I tell you, this generation will not pass away until all things are accomplished.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 21:33"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will by no means pass\naway."]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 21:34"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“So be careful, or your hearts will be loaded down with carousing, drunkenness, and cares of this life, and that day\nwill come on you suddenly. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 21:35"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For it will come like a snare on all those who dwell on the surface of all the earth.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 21:36"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Therefore be watchful all the time, praying that you may be counted worthy to escape all these things that will\nhappen, and to stand before the Son of Man.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 21:37"},"Every day Isa was teaching in the temple, and every night he would go out and spend the night on the mountain that is\ncalled Olivet. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 21:38"},"All the people came early in the morning to him in the temple to hear him.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"LUK 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 22:1"},"Now the feast of unleavened bread, which is called the Passover, was approaching.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 22:2"},"The chief priests and the scribes sought how they might put him to death, for they feared the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 22:3"},"Iblis entered into Yehuda, who was also called Iscariot, who was counted with the twelve.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 22:4"},"He went away, and talked with the chief priests and captains about how he might deliver him to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 22:5"},"They were glad, and agreed to give him money. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 22:6"},"He consented, and sought an opportunity to deliver him to them in the absence of the multitude.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 22:7"},"The day of unleavened bread came, on which the Passover must be sacrificed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 22:8"},"Isa sent Peter and Yuhanna, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Go and prepare the Passover for us, that we may\neat.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 22:9"},"They said to him, “Where do you want us to prepare?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 22:10"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Behold, when you have entered into the city, a man carrying a pitcher of water will meet you.\nFollow him into the house which he enters. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 22:11"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Tell the master of the house, ‘The Teacher says to you, “Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover with\nmy disciples?”’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 22:12"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["He will show you a large, furnished upper room. Make preparations\nthere.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 22:13"},"They went, found things as Isa had told them, and they prepared the Passover.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 22:14"},"When the hour had come, he sat down with the twelve apostles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 22:15"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I have earnestly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 22:16"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I tell you, I will no longer by any means eat of it until it is fulfilled in Allah’s\nKingdom.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 22:17"},"He received a cup, and when he had given thanks, he said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Take this, and share it amongst yourselves,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 22:18"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["for I tell you, I will not drink at all again from the fruit of the vine, until Allah’s Kingdom\ncomes.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 22:19"},"He took bread, and when he had given thanks, he broke, and gave it to them, saying,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This is my body which is given for you. Do this in memory of\nme.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 22:20"},"Likewise, he took the cup after supper, saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This cup is the new covenant in my blood, which is poured out for\nyou. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 22:21"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But behold, the hand of him who betrays me is with me on the table.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 22:22"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["The Son of Man indeed goes, as it has been determined, but woe to that man through whom he is\nbetrayed!”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 22:23"},"They began to question amongst themselves, which of them it was who would do this thing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 22:24"},"A dispute also arose amongst them, which of them was considered to be greatest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 22:25"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“The kings of the nations lord it over them, and those who have authority over them are called\n‘benefactors.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 22:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But not so with you. But one who is the greater amongst you, let him become as the younger, and one who is\ngoverning, as one who serves. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 22:27"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For who is greater, one who sits at the table, or one who serves? Isn’t it he who sits at the table? But I am\namongst you as one who serves. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 22:28"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["But you are those who have continued with me in my trials.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 22:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["I confer on you a kingdom, even as my Father conferred on me,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 22:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["that you may eat and drink at my table in my Kingdom. You will sit on thrones, judging the twelve tribes of\nIsrael.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 22:31"},"The Lord said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Shima’un, Shima’un, behold, Iblis asked to have all of you, that he might sift you as wheat,\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 22:32"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["but I prayed for you, that your faith wouldn’t fail. You, when once you have turned again, establish your\nbrothers.”"]},{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here may be also correctly translated “brothers and sisters” or\n“siblings.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 22:33"},"He said to him, “Lord, I am ready to go with you both to prison and to death!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 22:34"},"He said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“I tell you, Peter, the rooster will by no means crow today until you deny that you know me three\ntimes.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 22:35"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“When I sent you out without purse, wallet, and sandals, did you lack\nanything?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said, “Nothing.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 22:36"},"Then he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“But now, whoever has a purse, let him take it, and likewise a wallet. Whoever has none, let\nhim sell his cloak, and buy a sword. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 22:37"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For I tell you that this which is written must still be fulfilled in me: ‘He was counted with\ntransgressors.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["22:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 53:12"]}],"caller":"+"}," ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For that which concerns me has an\nend.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 22:38"},"They said, “Lord, behold, here are two swords.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“That is enough.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 22:39"},"He came out and went, as his custom was, to the Mount of Olives. His disciples also followed him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 22:40"},"When he was at the place, he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Pray that you don’t enter into\ntemptation.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 22:41"},"He was withdrawn from them about a stone’s throw, and he knelt down and prayed,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 22:42"},"saying, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Father, if you are willing, remove this cup from me. Nevertheless, not my will, but yours, be\ndone.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 22:43"},"An angel from heaven appeared to him, strengthening him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 22:44"},"Being in agony he prayed more earnestly. His sweat became like great drops of blood falling down on the ground.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 22:45"},"When he rose up from his prayer, he came to the disciples, and found them sleeping because of grief,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 22:46"},"and said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why do you sleep? Rise and pray that you may not enter into\ntemptation.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 22:47"},"While he was still speaking, behold, a multitude, and he who was called Yehuda, one of the twelve, was leading them. He\ncame near to Isa to kiss him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 22:48"},"But Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Yehuda, do you betray the Son of Man with a\nkiss?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 22:49"},"When those who were around him saw what was about to happen, they said to him, “Lord, shall we strike with the sword?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 22:50"},"A certain one of them struck the servant of the high priest, and cut off his right ear.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 22:51"},"But Isa answered, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Let me at least do this”"]},"—and he touched his ear, and healed him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 22:52"},"Isa said to the chief priests, captains of the temple, and elders, who had come against him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Have you come out as against a robber, with swords and clubs?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 22:53"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["When I was with you in the temple daily, you didn’t stretch out your hands against me. But this is your hour, and\nthe power of darkness.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 22:54"},"They seized him, and led him away, and brought him into the high priest’s house. But Peter followed from a distance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 22:55"},"When they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard, and had sat down together, Peter sat amongst them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 22:56"},"A certain servant girl saw him as he sat in the light, and looking intently at him, said, “This man also was with him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"LUK 22:57"},"He denied Isa, saying, “Woman, I don’t know him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"LUK 22:58"},"After a little while someone else saw him, and said, “You also are one of them!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Peter answered, “Man, I am not!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"LUK 22:59"},"After about one hour passed, another confidently affirmed, saying, “Truly this man also was with him, for he is a\nGalilean!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"LUK 22:60"},"But Peter said, “Man, I don’t know what you are talking about!” Immediately, while he was still speaking, a rooster\ncrowed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"LUK 22:61"},"The Lord turned and looked at Peter. Then Peter remembered the Lord’s word, how he said to him,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Before the rooster crows you will deny me three times.”"]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"LUK 22:62"},"He went out, and wept bitterly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"LUK 22:63"},"The men who held Isa mocked him and beat him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64","sid":"LUK 22:64"},"Having blindfolded him, they struck him on the face and asked him, “Prophesy! Who is the one who struck you?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65","sid":"LUK 22:65"},"They spoke many other things against him, insulting him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66","sid":"LUK 22:66"},"As soon as it was day, the assembly of the elders of the people were gathered together, both chief priests and scribes,\nand they led him away into their council, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67","sid":"LUK 22:67"},"“If you are the Masih, tell us.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But he said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“If I tell you, you won’t believe, "]},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68","sid":"LUK 22:68"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and if I ask, you will in no way answer me or let me go.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69","sid":"LUK 22:69"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["From now on, the Son of Man will be seated at the right hand of the power of\nAllah.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70","sid":"LUK 22:70"},"They all said, “Are you then the Son of Allah?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“You say it, because I am.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71","sid":"LUK 22:71"},"They said, “Why do we need any more witness? For we ourselves have heard from his own mouth!”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23","sid":"LUK 23"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 23:1"},"The whole company of them rose up and brought him before Pilate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 23:2"},"They began to accuse him, saying, “We found this man perverting the nation, forbidding paying taxes to Caesar, and saying\nthat he himself is Masih, a king.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 23:3"},"Pilate asked him, “Are you the King of the Jews?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He answered him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“So you say.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 23:4"},"Pilate said to the chief priests and the multitudes, “I find no basis for a charge against this man.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 23:5"},"But they insisted, saying, “He stirs up the people, teaching throughout all Judea, beginning from Galilee even to this\nplace.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 23:6"},"But when Pilate heard Galilee mentioned, he asked if the man was a Galilean.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 23:7"},"When he found out that he was in Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod, who was also in Jerusalem during those days.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 23:8"},"Now when Herod saw Isa, he was exceedingly glad, for he had wanted to see him for a long time, because he had heard many\nthings about him. He hoped to see some miracle done by him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 23:9"},"He questioned him with many words, but he gave no answers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 23:10"},"The chief priests and the scribes stood, vehemently accusing him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 23:11"},"Herod with his soldiers humiliated him and mocked him. Dressing him in luxurious clothing, they sent him back to Pilate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 23:12"},"Herod and Pilate became friends with each other that very day, for before that they were enemies with each other.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 23:13"},"Pilate called together the chief priests, the rulers, and the people,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 23:14"},"and said to them, “You brought this man to me as one that perverts the people, and behold, having examined him before\nyou, I found no basis for a charge against this man concerning those things of which you accuse him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 23:15"},"Neither has Herod, for I sent you to him, and see, nothing worthy of death has been done by him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 23:16"},"I will therefore chastise him and release him.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 23:17"},"Now he had to release one prisoner to them at the feast.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NU omits verse 17."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 23:18"},"But they all cried out together, saying, “Away with this man! Release to us Barabbas!”—\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 23:19"},"one who was thrown into prison for a certain revolt in the city, and for murder.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 23:20"},"Then Pilate spoke to them again, wanting to release Isa, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 23:21"},"but they shouted, saying, “Crucify! Crucify him!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 23:22"},"He said to them the third time, “Why? What evil has this man done? I have found no capital crime in him. I will therefore\nchastise him and release him.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 23:23"},"But they were urgent with loud voices, asking that he might be crucified. Their voices and the voices of the chief\npriests prevailed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 23:24"},"Pilate decreed that what they asked for should be done. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 23:25"},"He released him who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, for whom they asked, but he delivered Isa up\nto their will. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 23:26"},"When they led him away, they grabbed one Shima’un of Cyrene, coming from the country, and laid on him the cross, to carry\nit after Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 23:27"},"A great multitude of the people followed him, including women who also mourned and lamented him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 23:28"},"But Isa, turning to them, said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Daughters of Jerusalem, don’t weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your\nchildren. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 23:29"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For behold, the days are coming in which they will say, ‘Blessed are the barren, the wombs that never bore, and the\nbreasts that never nursed.’ "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 23:30"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Then they will begin to tell the mountains, ‘Fall on us!’ and tell the hills, ‘Cover\nus.’"]},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["23:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Hosea 10:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 23:31"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["For if they do these things in the green tree, what will be done in the\ndry?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 23:32"},"There were also others, two criminals, led with him to be put to death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 23:33"},"When they came to the place that is called “The Skull”, they crucified him there with the criminals, one on the right and\nthe other on the left. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 23:34"},"Isa said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Father, forgive them, for they don’t know what they are\ndoing.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Dividing his garments amongst them, they cast lots. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 23:35"},"The people stood watching. The rulers with them also scoffed at him, saying, “He saved others. Let him save himself, if\nthis is the Masih of Allah, his chosen one!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 23:36"},"The soldiers also mocked him, coming to him and offering him vinegar,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 23:37"},"and saying, “If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 23:38"},"An inscription was also written over him in letters of Greek, Latin, and Hebrew: “THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 23:39"},"One of the criminals who was hanged insulted him, saying, “If you are the Masih, save yourself and us!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 23:40"},"But the other answered, and rebuking him said, “Don’t you even fear Allah, seeing you are under the same condemnation?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 23:41"},"And we indeed justly, for we receive the due reward for our deeds, but this man has done nothing wrong.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 23:42"},"He said to Isa, “Lord, remember me when you come into your Kingdom.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 23:43"},"Isa said to him, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Assuredly I tell you, today you will be with me in\nParadise.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 23:44"},"It was now about the sixth hour,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Time was counted from sunrise, so the sixth hour was about\nnoon."]}],"caller":"+"}," and darkness came over the whole land until the ninth hour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:44 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["3:00 p.m."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 23:45"},"The sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was torn in two.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 23:46"},"Isa, crying with a loud voice, said, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Father, into your hands I commit my\nspirit!”"]}," Having said this, he breathed his last. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 23:47"},"When the centurion saw what was done, he glorified Allah, saying, “Certainly this was a righteous man.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 23:48"},"All the multitudes that came together to see this, when they saw the things that were done, returned home beating their\nbreasts. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 23:49"},"All his acquaintances and the women who followed with him from Galilee stood at a distance, watching these things.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 23:50"},"Behold, a man named Yusuf, who was a member of the council, a good and righteous man\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 23:51"},"(he had not consented to their counsel and deed), from Arimathaea, a city of the Jews, who was also waiting for Allah’s\nKingdom: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 23:52"},"this man went to Pilate, and asked for Isa’s body. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 23:53"},"He took it down, and wrapped it in a linen cloth, and laid him in a tomb that was cut in stone, where no one had ever\nbeen laid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"LUK 23:54"},"It was the day of the Preparation, and the Sabbath was drawing near.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"LUK 23:55"},"The women, who had come with him out of Galilee, followed after, and saw the tomb, and how his body was laid.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"LUK 23:56"},"They returned and prepared spices and ointments. On the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24","sid":"LUK 24"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"LUK 24:1"},"But on the first day of the week, at early dawn, they and some others came to the tomb, bringing the spices which they had\nprepared. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"LUK 24:2"},"They found the stone rolled away from the tomb. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"LUK 24:3"},"They entered in, and didn’t find the Lord Isa’s body. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"LUK 24:4"},"While they were greatly perplexed about this, behold, two men stood by them in dazzling clothing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"LUK 24:5"},"Becoming terrified, they bowed their faces down to the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said to them, “Why do you seek the living amongst the dead?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"LUK 24:6"},"He isn’t here, but is risen. Remember what he told you when he was still in Galilee,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"LUK 24:7"},"saying that the Son of Man must be delivered up into the hands of sinful men and be crucified, and the third day rise\nagain?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"LUK 24:8"},"They remembered his words, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"LUK 24:9"},"returned from the tomb, and told all these things to the eleven and to all the rest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"LUK 24:10"},"Now they were Maryam Magdalene, Joanna, and Maryam the mother of Yaqub. The other women with them told these things to\nthe apostles. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"LUK 24:11"},"These words seemed to them to be nonsense, and they didn’t believe them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"LUK 24:12"},"But Peter got up and ran to the tomb. Stooping and looking in, he saw the strips of linen lying by themselves, and he\ndeparted to his home, wondering what had happened. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"LUK 24:13"},"Behold, two of them were going that very day to a village named Emmaus, which was sixty\nstadia",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["60 stadia = about 11 kilometres or about 7 miles.\n"]}],"caller":"+"}," from Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"LUK 24:14"},"They talked with each other about all of these things which had happened.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"LUK 24:15"},"While they talked and questioned together, Isa himself came near, and went with them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"LUK 24:16"},"But their eyes were kept from recognising him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"LUK 24:17"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What are you talking about as you walk, and are\nsad?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"LUK 24:18"},"One of them, named Cleopas, answered him, “Are you the only stranger in Jerusalem who doesn’t know the things which have\nhappened there in these days?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"LUK 24:19"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“What things?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They said to him, “The things concerning Isa, the Nazarene, who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before Allah and all\nthe people; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"LUK 24:20"},"and how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him up to be condemned to death, and crucified him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"LUK 24:21"},"But we were hoping that it was he who would redeem Israel. Yes, and besides all this, it is now the third day since these\nthings happened. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"LUK 24:22"},"Also, certain women of our company amazed us, having arrived early at the tomb;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"LUK 24:23"},"and when they didn’t find his body, they came saying that they had also seen a vision of angels, who said that he was\nalive. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"LUK 24:24"},"Some of us went to the tomb, and found it just like the women had said, but they didn’t see him.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"LUK 24:25"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Foolish men, and slow of heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken!\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"LUK 24:26"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Didn’t the Masih have to suffer these things and to enter into his\nglory?”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"LUK 24:27"},"Beginning from Musa and from all the prophets, he explained to them in all the Scriptures the things concerning himself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"LUK 24:28"},"They came near to the village where they were going, and he acted like he would go further.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"LUK 24:29"},"They urged him, saying, “Stay with us, for it is almost evening, and the day is almost over.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He went in to stay with them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"LUK 24:30"},"When he had sat down at the table with them, he took the bread and gave thanks. Breaking it, he gave it to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"LUK 24:31"},"Their eyes were opened and they recognised him, then he vanished out of their sight.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"LUK 24:32"},"They said to one another, “Weren’t our hearts burning within us, while he spoke to us along the way, and while he opened\nthe Scriptures to us?” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"LUK 24:33"},"They rose up that very hour, returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together, and those who were with them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"LUK 24:34"},"saying, “The Lord is risen indeed, and has appeared to Shima’un!”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"LUK 24:35"},"They related the things that happened along the way, and how he was recognised by them in the breaking of the bread.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"LUK 24:36"},"As they said these things, Isa himself stood amongst them, and said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Peace be to you.”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"LUK 24:37"},"But they were terrified and filled with fear, and supposed that they had seen a spirit.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"LUK 24:38"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Why are you troubled? Why do doubts arise in your hearts?\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"LUK 24:39"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["See my hands and my feet, that it is truly me. Touch me and see, for a spirit doesn’t have flesh and bones, as you\nsee that I have.”"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"LUK 24:40"},"When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his feet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"LUK 24:41"},"While they still didn’t believe for joy, and wondered, he said to them,\n",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Do you have anything here to eat?”"]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"LUK 24:42"},"They gave him a piece of a broiled fish and some honeycomb.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"LUK 24:43"},"He took them, and ate in front of them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"LUK 24:44"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“This is what I told you, while I was still with you, that all things which are written in the law\nof Musa, the prophets, and the psalms, concerning me must be fulfilled.”"]},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"LUK 24:45"},"Then he opened their minds, that they might understand the Scriptures.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"LUK 24:46"},"He said to them, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“Thus it is written, and thus it was necessary for the Masih to suffer and to rise from the dead the\nthird day, "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"LUK 24:47"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["and that repentance and remission of sins should be preached in his name to all the nations, beginning at Jerusalem.\n"]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"LUK 24:48"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["You are witnesses of these things. "]}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"LUK 24:49"},{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["Behold, I send out the promise of my Father on you. But wait in the city of Jerusalem until you are clothed with\npower from on high.” "]}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"LUK 24:50"},"He led them out as far as Bethany, and he lifted up his hands, and blessed them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"LUK 24:51"},"While he blessed them, he withdrew from them, and was carried up into heaven.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"LUK 24:52"},"They worshipped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"LUK 24:53"},"and were continually in the temple, praising and blessing Allah. Amen.\n"]}]}